1
00:03:11,725 --> 00:03:15,604
Hang on, hang on. Come on.

2
00:03:17,147 --> 00:03:19,983
<i>Where are you, Charlie?
More importantly, where is my money?</i>

3
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:23,320
- You're into me for 30 grand.
- Jack, I'm going to pay you.

4
00:03:23,487 --> 00:03:25,864
<i>This ain't Jack! It's Bill Panner.</i>

5
00:03:26,031 --> 00:03:29,409
<i>You owe Jack money, too?
You pay me first!</i>

6
00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:34,248
Bill. We're good, buddy. I got your
money. It's right here in my hand.

7
00:03:34,414 --> 00:03:36,291
Why don't we meet up on the...?

8
00:03:41,004 --> 00:03:43,924
<i>- Your phone's going all screwy. Hello?</i>
- <i>I'm losing</i> you.

9
00:03:44,091 --> 00:03:46,468
<i>I can't hear what you're say...</i>

10
00:03:49,012 --> 00:03:51,723
Hey, mister. Is that Ambush?

11
00:03:53,392 --> 00:03:55,644
- Yeah.
- Can we see him?

12
00:03:57,062 --> 00:03:59,314
- You want to see him?
- Yeah.

13
00:03:59,481 --> 00:04:01,733
Give me a minute.

14
00:04:08,031 --> 00:04:09,158
This...

15
00:04:10,909 --> 00:04:13,453
is Ambush. Wakey, wakey.

16
00:04:33,515 --> 00:04:36,852
- What robot is he fighting?
- Actually he's going to fight...

17
00:04:37,019 --> 00:04:38,538
Whoa, little lady. What are you doing?

18
00:04:38,562 --> 00:04:39,897
Can we get a picture with him?

19
00:04:40,063 --> 00:04:41,607
Sure. For five dollars.

20
00:04:41,773 --> 00:04:43,901
You want five dollars? Seriously?

21
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:46,570
No, I want five dollars immediately.

22
00:04:46,737 --> 00:04:48,280
Come on, guys.

23
00:04:49,907 --> 00:04:53,243
- All right, I'm kidding. Three bucks.
- Whatever.

24
00:04:53,410 --> 00:04:56,163
- How about $2.50?
- You suck!

25
00:04:59,374 --> 00:05:01,752
It's going to be one
of those towns, huh?

26
00:05:02,753 --> 00:05:07,549
<i>Welcome, ladies and gentlemen,
to the 2020 San Leandro County Fair.</i>

27
00:05:07,716 --> 00:05:11,261
<i>Please take your seats. We're almost
ready to get this thing started.</i>

28
00:05:13,430 --> 00:05:15,933
I was told my bot
was fighting an 800-pound steer.

29
00:05:16,099 --> 00:05:18,685
That is not 800 pounds, Knucklehead.

30
00:05:18,852 --> 00:05:23,774
Charlie "the Can Do Kid" Kenton. Time
has not been good to you, my friend.

31
00:05:23,941 --> 00:05:28,445
- Ricky, we got a big problem here.
- Slow down there, hoss.

32
00:05:28,612 --> 00:05:33,242
Last time I saw you, you were staring
at the ceiling at the Sam Houston Center

33
00:05:33,408 --> 00:05:35,702
with the taste of my right cross
all over your face.

34
00:05:37,913 --> 00:05:39,623
- Are we good to go here?
- Yeah.

35
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:43,627
We agreed that my boxer would fight
an 800-pound steer for three grand.

36
00:05:43,794 --> 00:05:45,420
- Am I right?
- Yes, sir. We did.

37
00:05:45,587 --> 00:05:47,547
That bull is like 2,000 pounds.

38
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,299
I'll tell you something.

39
00:05:49,466 --> 00:05:53,679
Your bot don't fight,
you don't get paid! How about that?

40
00:05:55,597 --> 00:05:57,224
Get the hell out of here.

41
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:04,815
Why don't we make this more interesting.
My bot against your bull, straight up.

42
00:06:04,982 --> 00:06:07,025
- How much?
- Twenty grand, winner takes all.

43
00:06:07,192 --> 00:06:09,736
- Twenty grand. You got 20 grand?
- In a safe in my truck.

44
00:06:13,323 --> 00:06:14,700
All right, Charlie.

45
00:06:14,866 --> 00:06:18,996
Twenty grand it is,
but if you lose and you welch,

46
00:06:19,162 --> 00:06:21,641
I'll come after you and beat you
to within an inch of your life.

47
00:06:21,665 --> 00:06:23,977
You know that I can do that
because I already done done it!

48
00:06:24,001 --> 00:06:27,754
In life you get too close, in the ring
you stand back like a girl. Just shake.

49
00:06:28,171 --> 00:06:33,010
All right. Shake and pow! Just like that
once again. You want to dance again?

50
00:06:33,176 --> 00:06:36,513
Cheer for this guy. Give him some luck.
He needs some luck, y'all.

51
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:39,599
Don't touch that bull.

52
00:06:39,766 --> 00:06:42,853
Ladies and gentlemen, I got to ask,

53
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:45,439
do we have any fans
of robot boxing here today?

54
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:50,277
Now, listen, friends, I understand

55
00:06:50,444 --> 00:06:54,197
we can't all afford to go
all the way over there to Dallas

56
00:06:54,364 --> 00:06:59,202
and pay $300 for one of those
World Robot Boxing League fights.

57
00:06:59,369 --> 00:07:02,497
So, I decided that I would bring
a robot boxing match

58
00:07:02,664 --> 00:07:06,043
right hereto our little fair
here in San Leandro.

59
00:07:06,209 --> 00:07:07,461
How about that?

60
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:14,718
Ladies and gentlemen,
I introduce to you,

61
00:07:14,885 --> 00:07:17,429
Ambush!

62
00:07:17,596 --> 00:07:18,930
Let's do it!

63
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,934
All right, big fella.

64
00:07:28,565 --> 00:07:30,359
He's a big fella, ain't he?

65
00:07:30,525 --> 00:07:34,029
Take a turn.
Let them see how beautiful you are.

66
00:07:38,784 --> 00:07:39,868
Show them some power.

67
00:07:41,078 --> 00:07:43,789
Look at that.
He's getting all kung fu-y on us.

68
00:07:45,082 --> 00:07:46,375
Yeah, big fella.

69
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:49,586
Ambush's opponent today,
he's last year's runner-up

70
00:07:49,753 --> 00:07:51,755
in the baddest of the bulls competition,

71
00:07:51,922 --> 00:07:54,674
ladies and gentlemen,

72
00:07:54,841 --> 00:07:57,552
Black Thunder!

73
00:07:59,096 --> 00:08:01,681
- Let's get it on!
- Let's get this thing started.

74
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:06,937
Is that all you got?

75
00:08:08,146 --> 00:08:10,941
Yeah, brother. Bring it on.

76
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:22,327
Take him, take him.

77
00:08:23,787 --> 00:08:27,290
Ambush lays the smackdown
on that prime beef.

78
00:08:33,130 --> 00:08:35,411
I got more for you, big fella.
We're just getting started.

79
00:08:38,552 --> 00:08:40,137
OK. Jump, now!

80
00:08:48,228 --> 00:08:49,729
Ambush, decks Black Thunder,

81
00:08:49,896 --> 00:08:53,275
but when you mess with the bull,
you're going to get the horns.

82
00:08:56,069 --> 00:08:58,405
You like that. I can tell.
You like that.

83
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,491
Turn around!

84
00:09:05,287 --> 00:09:07,747
Ricky! Ricky, stop this thing!

85
00:09:18,008 --> 00:09:20,844
Come on. We're still in this thing.
Just hop. Hop.

86
00:09:22,179 --> 00:09:23,346
That's it. Come on.

87
00:09:27,517 --> 00:09:29,978
Ricky, enough! Enough!

88
00:09:30,145 --> 00:09:33,315
I can't hear you over the sound
of your robot being destroyed.

89
00:09:34,691 --> 00:09:36,818
Kill! Kill! Kill!

90
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,488
Come on, get up.

91
00:09:40,447 --> 00:09:41,740
Get up! Come on!

92
00:09:45,452 --> 00:09:46,453
No!

93
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:53,251
Come on, no. No, no, no!

94
00:09:59,549 --> 00:10:03,053
Ladies and gentlemen, let's hear it
for our warriors out here today

95
00:10:03,220 --> 00:10:05,764
at the 2020 San Leandro County Fair.

96
00:10:05,931 --> 00:10:07,849
Thank you for coming out,

97
00:10:08,016 --> 00:10:11,603
and we'll see you next time,
because there will be one.

98
00:10:12,729 --> 00:10:13,730
Give me that leg.

99
00:10:13,897 --> 00:10:15,732
Sure. For five dollars.

100
00:10:15,899 --> 00:10:17,567
<i>Boo-yaw.!</i>

101
00:10:19,486 --> 00:10:24,199
All right! That was ridonculous fun,
now wasn't it, ladies and gentlemen?

102
00:10:25,325 --> 00:10:28,703
I'm going to come by for my money,
Charlie boy. You best have it.

103
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,914
- Everybody say "hey!"
- Hey!

104
00:10:31,081 --> 00:10:34,751
FY who!"
" Ho!

105
00:10:34,918 --> 00:10:38,129
How about that?
How you doing there, little robot?

106
00:10:54,854 --> 00:10:56,523
My keys, damn it.

107
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,520
One more step
and I'll drop you like your girlfriend.

108
00:10:59,609 --> 00:11:00,694
Charlie, relax.

109
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:03,780
I'm not paying you. That was a bogus
fight. It cost me my last robot.

110
00:11:03,947 --> 00:11:06,783
- Just listen to us.
- Do you recall Caroline Fallon?

111
00:11:07,534 --> 00:11:10,534
She's my ex-girlfriend. I haven't seen
her in ten years. What does she want?

112
00:11:10,620 --> 00:11:12,289
Nothing. She died.

113
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:14,583
Do you recall Max Kenton?

114
00:11:16,293 --> 00:11:18,128
He's my son. He's got to be nine.

115
00:11:18,295 --> 00:11:19,921
- Eleven.
- Eleven. OK.

116
00:11:21,590 --> 00:11:22,924
Is he dead, too?

117
00:11:23,091 --> 00:11:25,802
No, he's fine. That's why we're here.

118
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:55,832
This court is convened
to address the custodial status

119
00:11:55,999 --> 00:11:58,293
of one Max Kenton, age 11.

120
00:11:58,460 --> 00:12:02,922
Mother, Caroline Fallon, deceased.
Father, Charles Kenton.

121
00:12:03,089 --> 00:12:05,133
Debra Fallon Barnes,
you're the boy's aunt.

122
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:10,597
Yes. As I've already told you,
my husband, Marvin, is wealthy,

123
00:12:10,764 --> 00:12:14,184
and we can more than provide for Max.

124
00:12:14,351 --> 00:12:17,729
I appreciate that, but per Texas
state law, without a written will

125
00:12:17,896 --> 00:12:19,773
next of kin retains custody.

126
00:12:19,939 --> 00:12:23,109
Charles Kenton,
who is aware of this custody hearing,

127
00:12:23,276 --> 00:12:24,653
and we are expecting him...

128
00:12:24,819 --> 00:12:27,280
I need a new robot now.

129
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:29,783
I had a big fight
for Ambush next Saturday.

130
00:12:29,949 --> 00:12:31,326
I got to show up with something.

131
00:12:31,493 --> 00:12:36,289
Noisy Boy is for sale?
In his day, Noisy Boy was a killer.

132
00:12:36,456 --> 00:12:39,042
How much? That's a good deal.
What's wrong with him?

133
00:12:40,210 --> 00:12:41,544
I can live with that.

134
00:12:42,879 --> 00:12:44,255
I don't have it.

135
00:12:44,422 --> 00:12:48,468
Charles Kenton waived all of his rights
to custody right after the boy was born.

136
00:12:48,635 --> 00:12:51,137
I can more than provide for Max.

137
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:54,724
Please be Charles Kenton.

138
00:12:57,519 --> 00:12:59,229
Charlie, yeah.

139
00:13:00,563 --> 00:13:02,899
I'm hereto sign some paper
that releases my rights

140
00:13:03,066 --> 00:13:04,984
to the custody of my son.

141
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:07,070
That's why I'm here.
Do I need to be here?

142
00:13:07,237 --> 00:13:08,530
Charlie.

143
00:13:09,572 --> 00:13:10,907
Do you even remember me?

144
00:13:11,908 --> 00:13:14,285
- Debra, Carmine's sister.
- Yeah, Debra. How are you?

145
00:13:14,452 --> 00:13:16,371
Mr Kenton. Please take a seat.

146
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:22,836
Your Honour, may I please go
and see my nephew now?

147
00:13:23,002 --> 00:13:24,045
Yes, you may.

148
00:13:24,212 --> 00:13:25,922
- How about you, Mr Kenton?
- What?

149
00:13:26,089 --> 00:13:28,591
You can spend some time
with him, if you'd like.

150
00:13:28,758 --> 00:13:30,385
- With the kid?
- Yeah, the kid.

151
00:13:30,552 --> 00:13:32,345
- Max. Your son?
- All right.

152
00:13:32,512 --> 00:13:35,265
You've been working with those robots
for so long, you've become one.

153
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:38,936
Honey, you wait right here.
I'm going to be back.

154
00:13:39,102 --> 00:13:41,604
You take all the time you need,
sweetheart.

155
00:13:46,901 --> 00:13:50,113
Your Honour, I'd like to,
at this juncture,

156
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,824
step out and call my attorney,
if that's all right.

157
00:13:52,991 --> 00:13:53,992
Please.

158
00:13:57,787 --> 00:14:01,958
Come on. Come on. There you are.

159
00:14:02,959 --> 00:14:05,795
He'll be in a foster home.

160
00:14:05,962 --> 00:14:10,008
No, they find good families.
Young. Energetic. Yeah.

161
00:14:11,259 --> 00:14:14,804
Thanks, Michael. I will. OK.

162
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:21,019
- Marvin Barnes. I'm Debra's husband.
- Right, yeah.

163
00:14:21,186 --> 00:14:24,147
Debra really wants to adopt Max.

164
00:14:26,691 --> 00:14:29,569
- I'm up for it. But...
- Seventy-five grand.

165
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:33,823
$75,000? You're serious?

166
00:14:36,493 --> 00:14:37,994
The thing is...

167
00:14:39,037 --> 00:14:41,247
we're supposed to go
to Italy this summer

168
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:43,082
with my oldest friend and his wife.

169
00:14:43,249 --> 00:14:45,335
Two months in Tuscany and all over.

170
00:14:45,502 --> 00:14:46,862
Just the four of you. Sounds nice.

171
00:14:47,003 --> 00:14:49,297
We'll be back in New York
by the end of August.

172
00:14:50,089 --> 00:14:53,218
In August. A hundred.

173
00:14:53,384 --> 00:14:55,303
- $100,000?
- You heard me.

174
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:57,680
- You're crazy.
- Not nearly as crazy as your wife

175
00:14:57,847 --> 00:15:01,184
if you tell her I just signed over
that kid to the state of Texas.

176
00:15:01,351 --> 00:15:04,896
There's a real way everyone gets
what they want here.

177
00:15:05,063 --> 00:15:07,190
So here's what you're going to do.

178
00:15:07,357 --> 00:15:10,401
You're going to tell your wife
I'll only sign over custody to her

179
00:15:10,568 --> 00:15:12,695
if I get to spend the summer
with the kid first.

180
00:15:12,862 --> 00:15:15,281
Just tell her how guilty
she made me feel

181
00:15:15,448 --> 00:15:17,700
for being such
a terrible absentee dad,

182
00:15:17,867 --> 00:15:21,913
how I want to make good with junior,
a little fatherly bonding, whatnot.

183
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,959
She'll buy it, you get to be the hero
and everybody wins.

184
00:15:29,003 --> 00:15:32,757
OK. But not a word about the money
to Debra, you understand?

185
00:15:33,842 --> 00:15:35,301
I understand.

186
00:15:35,468 --> 00:15:37,720
I'll give you 50 grand tonight
when we drop off Max

187
00:15:37,887 --> 00:15:40,181
and the other 50
when we get back in August

188
00:15:40,348 --> 00:15:42,141
and you deliver him to us in New York.

189
00:15:42,809 --> 00:15:44,519
Pleasure doing business with you.

190
00:15:47,355 --> 00:15:49,607
Your Honour,
I'm happy we all took the time

191
00:15:49,774 --> 00:15:51,334
to make the best decision for everyone.

192
00:15:54,863 --> 00:15:56,364
- Happy?
- Yeah, it's me.

193
00:15:56,531 --> 00:15:59,742
I'm buying Noisy Boy. I got the money.

194
00:15:59,909 --> 00:16:02,453
Take him to Tallet's Gym
and I'll meet you there.

195
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:18,761
Hello?

196
00:16:19,971 --> 00:16:21,264
Bailey?

197
00:16:21,431 --> 00:16:23,231
Some guy is here
with the robot you're buying,

198
00:16:23,266 --> 00:16:25,518
and it smells like disaster to me.

199
00:16:25,685 --> 00:16:27,020
Nice to see you, too.

200
00:16:27,186 --> 00:16:30,023
- Might I also say how cute you look.
- Give it up.

201
00:16:30,189 --> 00:16:33,693
God, I need a shower.
You want to take a shower? Come on.

202
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:35,612
Let me make something clear.

203
00:16:35,778 --> 00:16:38,615
A creepy dude with a robot in a box

204
00:16:38,781 --> 00:16:41,075
has been sitting outside my gym
for two hours.

205
00:16:41,242 --> 00:16:43,077
Putting aside the fact
that you're doing

206
00:16:43,244 --> 00:16:45,955
what I'm guessing is
a black market deal on my doorstep,

207
00:16:46,122 --> 00:16:48,162
how will you pay him
when Ambush just got destroyed?

208
00:16:48,249 --> 00:16:50,084
The money is on its way.
Just distract him.

209
00:16:50,251 --> 00:16:51,628
I have been. It's exhausting.

210
00:16:51,794 --> 00:16:53,630
- You're the best.
- Yeah? Really?

211
00:16:53,796 --> 00:16:56,799
Is that why you're buying a $45,000
robot when you owe me six grand in rent?

212
00:16:56,966 --> 00:16:58,301
- Because I'm the best?
- Three.

213
00:16:58,468 --> 00:17:03,723
Six. There is a guy with real money
who wants to buy this place.

214
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:06,130
Come on. Like you're really
going to sell your dad's gym.

215
00:17:06,225 --> 00:17:09,312
If you don't make rent, I can't make
payments and I won't have a choice.

216
00:17:09,479 --> 00:17:11,457
Your father would climb out of his grave
and kick your ass

217
00:17:11,481 --> 00:17:13,375
- if you sold this place.
- My father would climb out of his grave

218
00:17:13,399 --> 00:17:14,734
and kick your ass.

219
00:17:17,403 --> 00:17:18,404
Bailey?

220
00:17:24,535 --> 00:17:25,536
- Don't.
- Don't what?

221
00:17:25,703 --> 00:17:27,163
Don't do that.

222
00:17:29,290 --> 00:17:31,292
- Don't what?
- Don't do that thing.

223
00:17:34,003 --> 00:17:35,713
- No, you like that thing.
- No.

224
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:38,007
- Yeah.
- No, I don't like that thing.

225
00:17:38,174 --> 00:17:42,053
I used to. Once. Briefly.
Now I like money more.

226
00:17:42,971 --> 00:17:45,974
- I don't believe you.
- I don't care.

227
00:17:48,393 --> 00:17:49,394
Marvin.

228
00:17:50,478 --> 00:17:52,522
Your money has arrived.

229
00:17:54,899 --> 00:17:55,900
<i>Maw .</i>

230
00:18:00,363 --> 00:18:02,532
Fifty grand, as promised.

231
00:18:03,408 --> 00:18:08,621
Here are all our numbers
and contact info over in Europe.

232
00:18:08,788 --> 00:18:10,415
So that's everything there.

233
00:18:13,376 --> 00:18:16,170
So Marvin tells me
you want this time with Max.

234
00:18:16,838 --> 00:18:18,548
- Yeah.
- You did the right thing,

235
00:18:18,715 --> 00:18:19,841
giving me custody.

236
00:18:20,008 --> 00:18:21,342
Caroline would have wanted that.

237
00:18:22,719 --> 00:18:25,221
Now, have him back in New York
on August 27th.

238
00:18:26,597 --> 00:18:27,849
That's a deal.

239
00:18:28,516 --> 00:18:32,437
OK, let's go get Max.
OK? Let's get Max.

240
00:18:35,815 --> 00:18:39,402
It's OK. You want to go around
the other side here and I'll get Max?

241
00:18:41,029 --> 00:18:44,365
Hey. Max. See you, pal.

242
00:18:45,408 --> 00:18:47,952
Max, we'll see you
at the end of the summer, honey.

243
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,255
I'm Charlie.

244
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,887
It's been a long time.
You know, I'm your...

245
00:19:06,054 --> 00:19:08,097
- You screwed me.
- Nice mouth.

246
00:19:08,264 --> 00:19:09,408
Do you know where they're going?

247
00:19:09,432 --> 00:19:11,309
- Italy?
- Yeah, Italy.

248
00:19:11,476 --> 00:19:12,953
So how did I get stuck here with you?

249
00:19:12,977 --> 00:19:15,813
Relax, kid. You got a whole life
of fine living ahead of you.

250
00:19:15,980 --> 00:19:16,981
Charlie!

251
00:19:17,857 --> 00:19:19,609
Dude's pissed. He's going to take off.

252
00:19:21,402 --> 00:19:23,905
- Did Marvin give you that money?
- Here, just close the deal.

253
00:19:24,072 --> 00:19:25,573
I'll be right there, OK?

254
00:19:30,787 --> 00:19:32,663
- I'm Bailey.
- Max.

255
00:19:34,457 --> 00:19:35,792
Max Kenton.

256
00:19:37,376 --> 00:19:39,128
- So this is your...
- Yeah, it's him.

257
00:19:39,295 --> 00:19:40,630
Don't worry about it, OK?

258
00:19:41,631 --> 00:19:43,216
I'm looking at you two and...

259
00:19:43,382 --> 00:19:45,676
Just go and put Noisy
in the shop, please? Thank you.

260
00:19:52,683 --> 00:19:54,745
You're going to stay here with her
while I'm on the road.

261
00:19:54,769 --> 00:19:57,522
- How much did he give you?
- You're coming at this the wrong way.

262
00:19:57,688 --> 00:19:59,357
No, tell me. I want to know.

263
00:20:00,399 --> 00:20:02,735
Fifty thousand, OK?

264
00:20:02,902 --> 00:20:05,238
He gave me $50,000
to sign you over to her.

265
00:20:05,404 --> 00:20:06,864
Will you shut up now?

266
00:20:07,532 --> 00:20:08,658
You sold me?

267
00:20:10,118 --> 00:20:11,452
Sounds worse than it is.

268
00:20:11,619 --> 00:20:14,247
- Really.
- It's to take care of you.

269
00:20:14,413 --> 00:20:15,974
Give me half the money
and you won't have to.

270
00:20:15,998 --> 00:20:18,668
- Where are you going to go?
- Give me the money. I'll be fine.

271
00:20:18,835 --> 00:20:21,230
I told your aunt I'll get you
to New York at the end of the summer.

272
00:20:21,254 --> 00:20:22,755
Now you're concerned for Aunt Debra?

273
00:20:23,506 --> 00:20:26,134
You sold me for 50 grand.
You owe me half!

274
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:30,555
I don't have it! I spent the money
on a robot. It's gone! OK? Gone!

275
00:20:30,721 --> 00:20:32,056
I'm through here.

276
00:20:40,773 --> 00:20:42,692
What do we got?

277
00:20:42,859 --> 00:20:44,527
Noisy Boy has arrived.

278
00:20:45,278 --> 00:20:48,114
That's a lot of airline stickers
and customs tags.

279
00:20:48,281 --> 00:20:51,826
- He's been all over the world.
- London, Japan, Brazil, Sao Paulo...

280
00:20:51,993 --> 00:20:54,453
Hasn't seen North American soil
in over two years.

281
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:56,747
Maybe that's why you got
such a good price, genius.

282
00:21:00,042 --> 00:21:01,377
Decided to stay?

283
00:21:02,211 --> 00:21:05,173
This is Bailey. She'll be looking
after you for a few weeks.

284
00:21:05,339 --> 00:21:08,009
I need you to look after the kid
for a few weeks.

285
00:21:08,176 --> 00:21:10,887
- I want half that money.
- Are we back to this again?

286
00:21:12,722 --> 00:21:14,557
Is there a real robot boxer in there?

287
00:21:14,724 --> 00:21:16,444
Noisy Boy's in there.
You ever heard of him?

288
00:21:16,475 --> 00:21:20,062
Of course. He fought Rubicon
for the WRB belt in 2016.

289
00:21:26,319 --> 00:21:28,321
Holy crap, he looks amazing.

290
00:21:30,323 --> 00:21:34,202
His composite armour has been replaced.
Let's see if the insides look as good.

291
00:21:34,368 --> 00:21:37,955
I've watched that fight
with Rubicon like 20 times.

292
00:21:38,122 --> 00:21:39,874
He should have had him
in the third round,

293
00:21:40,041 --> 00:21:42,710
but Rubicon got lucky
with a huge right and ended it.

294
00:21:56,766 --> 00:21:58,726
Relax, kid, he's on our side.

295
00:21:58,893 --> 00:22:00,770
- Not funny.
- Kind of funny.

296
00:22:00,937 --> 00:22:02,537
You know he has voice recognition,
right?

297
00:22:02,605 --> 00:22:04,325
- No, he doesn't.
- He didn't in the League.

298
00:22:04,482 --> 00:22:06,543
When Noisy fought in Brazil,
they must have put it in.

299
00:22:06,567 --> 00:22:09,111
Brazilians are crazy
about that talk-to-your-robot crap.

300
00:22:12,073 --> 00:22:13,699
Right, left, uppercut!

301
00:22:17,286 --> 00:22:20,915
Doesn't work. Right, left, uppercut!

302
00:22:21,082 --> 00:22:23,363
I knew that price was too good
to be true. We got screwed.

303
00:22:23,459 --> 00:22:25,962
- Let me see if I can fix it.
- Look how good he looks, too.

304
00:22:26,128 --> 00:22:28,089
Give me two seconds.
Let me look at something!

305
00:22:28,256 --> 00:22:30,424
- Why didn't you ask to look at it?
- Relax!

306
00:22:35,638 --> 00:22:37,431
Was that Japanese?

307
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:44,146
Let me see if I can reset him
to English.

308
00:22:44,313 --> 00:22:45,815
How do you know Japanese?

309
00:22:45,982 --> 00:22:47,400
Video games.

310
00:22:48,359 --> 00:22:50,152
You play video games in Japanese?

311
00:22:50,319 --> 00:22:51,988
Japanese bootlegs are always better.

312
00:22:57,827 --> 00:22:59,203
Give me that.

313
00:23:00,246 --> 00:23:02,581
He's reset to English,
and I found his command matrix.

314
00:23:02,748 --> 00:23:05,001
They have pre-loaded
a bunch of combinations.

315
00:23:05,167 --> 00:23:07,503
They should be listed here.

316
00:23:09,922 --> 00:23:10,923
Top salvo!

317
00:23:14,135 --> 00:23:15,219
What did I tell you?

318
00:23:16,512 --> 00:23:18,139
Gravity One Downtown!

319
00:23:22,685 --> 00:23:24,478
I was due for some good luck!

320
00:23:24,645 --> 00:23:26,188
- You're welcome.
- Thank you.

321
00:23:26,355 --> 00:23:29,275
Bailey, help me put him in the truck.
I am going to go and get your money.

322
00:23:42,955 --> 00:23:45,041
- Give me the keys.
- I'm coming with you.

323
00:23:45,207 --> 00:23:46,876
- No, you're not.
- Why not?

324
00:23:47,043 --> 00:23:48,836
Because I don't want you with me, OK?

325
00:23:49,003 --> 00:23:52,757
I'm either coming with you, or you're
fishing for your keys in the sewer.

326
00:23:52,923 --> 00:23:55,718
Your choice.
What's it going to be, old man?

327
00:23:56,802 --> 00:23:59,513
Oh, my God. That was close, wasn't it?

328
00:24:01,223 --> 00:24:03,976
- Don't do that again.
- That's scaring you, isn't it?

329
00:24:04,143 --> 00:24:05,728
Don't do this again?

330
00:24:06,395 --> 00:24:08,731
Get in. Just get in.
Give me the keys first.

331
00:24:08,898 --> 00:24:11,442
Wait till I get in the truck.
Thanks, Big Pops.

332
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:19,408
Sweet ride.

333
00:24:19,575 --> 00:24:22,244
Put on your seatbelt and don't talk.

334
00:24:43,391 --> 00:24:45,768
I'm taking all bets!

335
00:25:11,293 --> 00:25:13,087
Keep up. Stay close.

336
00:25:16,632 --> 00:25:19,176
Charlie Kenton is in the house!

337
00:25:19,343 --> 00:25:21,762
- All right, all right.
- Come on, man!

338
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:25,850
- Is that Noisy Boy?
- The one and only.

339
00:25:26,016 --> 00:25:27,977
That's Noisy Boy!

340
00:25:32,356 --> 00:25:34,859
Noisy's been in Japan.
Softer bots over there.

341
00:25:35,025 --> 00:25:37,278
- Sure you want to fight him tonight?
- What do you got?

342
00:25:37,445 --> 00:25:39,572
He can take any bot in this place.
You know it.

343
00:25:41,115 --> 00:25:42,783
You can have any undercard you want.

344
00:25:42,950 --> 00:25:44,285
Five thousand guaranteed.

345
00:25:44,452 --> 00:25:47,329
A thousand every round
your bot survives.

346
00:25:47,496 --> 00:25:49,331
Fight till the death!

347
00:25:52,084 --> 00:25:54,420
No. Give me the main event.

348
00:25:54,587 --> 00:25:56,755
- Come on.
- This is Noisy Boy.

349
00:25:56,922 --> 00:25:58,466
An original Tak Mashido bot.

350
00:25:58,632 --> 00:26:01,302
He was a World Robot League boxer.
Come on!

351
00:26:04,054 --> 00:26:05,890
You want to fight Midas?

352
00:26:06,056 --> 00:26:09,185
Fifty thousand guaranteed,
winner takes all.

353
00:26:10,603 --> 00:26:13,689
Fifty? Really, 50? Now you're talking.

354
00:26:13,856 --> 00:26:15,691
Listen, listen. No, look.

355
00:26:15,858 --> 00:26:17,485
- Listen!
- Give me a sec.

356
00:26:17,651 --> 00:26:20,863
We should take an undercard fight,
make a little cash and get out of here!

357
00:26:21,030 --> 00:26:22,323
First, there is no "we."

358
00:26:22,490 --> 00:26:25,659
Second, he's going to crush Midas,
and I'm going to make real cash!

359
00:26:26,619 --> 00:26:28,454
We'll take Midas!

360
00:26:40,799 --> 00:26:43,677
Tonight, our main event

361
00:26:43,844 --> 00:26:48,766
features the gold-blooded killer!

362
00:26:50,226 --> 00:26:52,728
This pimped-out punk

363
00:26:52,895 --> 00:26:56,565
is programmed for pain!

364
00:26:57,399 --> 00:27:02,404
I give to you the mighty Midas!

365
00:27:43,279 --> 00:27:46,115
Against a bot

366
00:27:46,282 --> 00:27:51,036
who ran with the big boys in the WRB!

367
00:27:51,954 --> 00:27:57,084
He's been on an exile tour overseas,
but now he's back home,

368
00:27:57,251 --> 00:27:59,545
and he's ready to make some noise!

369
00:27:59,712 --> 00:28:03,382
Take your first look in a long time

370
00:28:03,549 --> 00:28:08,220
at Noisy Boy!

371
00:28:45,799 --> 00:28:47,926
Crash Palace,

372
00:28:48,093 --> 00:28:52,931
who's ready for some destruction?!

373
00:28:54,141 --> 00:28:57,686
Let's make some money! Come on!

374
00:28:57,853 --> 00:29:00,606
We have Midas against Noisy Boy.

375
00:29:00,773 --> 00:29:02,775
Noisy Boy against Midas.

376
00:29:02,941 --> 00:29:06,195
You've been waiting all night
for this matchup, Crash Palace!

377
00:29:12,534 --> 00:29:13,744
Scimitar right!

378
00:29:16,914 --> 00:29:18,540
Did you see that?

379
00:29:18,707 --> 00:29:21,835
Easy money, easy money all night.
All night long!

380
00:29:22,002 --> 00:29:25,130
Come on! It's not over yet. Let's go!

381
00:29:25,881 --> 00:29:27,341
Skull salvo! Firefight!

382
00:29:30,052 --> 00:29:33,055
- Yeah! Go, Noisy!
- Undercard, huh?

383
00:29:35,724 --> 00:29:36,850
Shockfist!

384
00:29:40,145 --> 00:29:41,897
Get in there. Shogun Trinity!

385
00:29:43,482 --> 00:29:45,734
Let's finish him. Gravity Slam, Uptown!

386
00:29:49,154 --> 00:29:50,739
This son-of-a-bitch is crazy!

387
00:29:53,242 --> 00:29:55,411
Full Metal Feud! Bring it!

388
00:29:58,997 --> 00:30:00,666
Southpaw! Pain Revolution!

389
00:30:02,251 --> 00:30:03,252
I got something for you.

390
00:30:04,586 --> 00:30:07,548
Don't you run from me!
You can't run from me!

391
00:30:09,591 --> 00:30:10,759
Get up!

392
00:30:13,887 --> 00:30:14,972
That's illegal!

393
00:30:15,139 --> 00:30:17,266
This is the underworld.
There are no rules!

394
00:30:18,225 --> 00:30:19,727
Now we're seeing the Midas touch.

395
00:30:19,893 --> 00:30:21,103
No. Hands up!

396
00:30:21,270 --> 00:30:24,273
Get back in that corner, bitch,
and take this whooping like a man!

397
00:30:28,235 --> 00:30:29,862
He's getting killed in there!

398
00:30:32,364 --> 00:30:36,660
It's a headset! You talk into it
and you tell him what to do!

399
00:30:36,827 --> 00:30:38,120
Panic Shield!

400
00:30:39,079 --> 00:30:41,123
That's it. One-Two Overlord!

401
00:30:45,294 --> 00:30:47,880
No, no. Shatter Punch!

402
00:30:52,134 --> 00:30:53,927
- Five Recall!
- Get some!

403
00:31:00,142 --> 00:31:01,143
Jab, jab!

404
00:31:08,567 --> 00:31:09,651
Right roundhouse!

405
00:31:09,818 --> 00:31:13,155
Did he just spit his juice
in Midas's face?

406
00:31:13,322 --> 00:31:15,866
No, you did not spit in Midas's face!

407
00:31:16,033 --> 00:31:18,410
It's party time now, Crash Palace!

408
00:31:18,577 --> 00:31:19,661
Use your left!

409
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:22,414
Noisy's trying to do something
with his one arm!

410
00:31:22,581 --> 00:31:25,751
But Midas pins him,
and Daddy goes to work!

411
00:31:31,256 --> 00:31:33,509
No, no! Get up!

412
00:31:35,177 --> 00:31:36,220
Get some!

413
00:31:38,096 --> 00:31:40,015
Move! Get out of the corner!

414
00:31:40,182 --> 00:31:43,560
Midas! Midas! Midas!

415
00:31:45,312 --> 00:31:48,857
Somebody's ready
to serve up a decappuccino!

416
00:31:49,024 --> 00:31:51,026
I got something for you! You ready?

417
00:31:52,945 --> 00:31:56,448
Good night! That's a home run for Midas.

418
00:31:56,615 --> 00:31:59,368
And so long to Noisy Boy.

419
00:32:31,525 --> 00:32:33,235
That sucked. You hungry?

420
00:32:34,820 --> 00:32:37,072
I saved what's left
of Noisy's voice recognition board.

421
00:32:37,239 --> 00:32:39,992
Other than that, he's trash.
I got to get a new robot together.

422
00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:42,911
I need to find a mainframe. What?

423
00:32:43,078 --> 00:32:45,372
- I hate hamburgers.
- What kid hates burgers?

424
00:32:45,539 --> 00:32:48,876
Fine. More for me. Here, drink this.

425
00:32:49,042 --> 00:32:50,711
You never should have taken that fight.

426
00:32:50,878 --> 00:32:53,005
Really? Really? Thanks, genius.

427
00:32:53,171 --> 00:32:56,508
Do you even think about the stuff you do
before you do it?

428
00:32:56,675 --> 00:32:58,927
You had no idea how to fight that fight.

429
00:32:59,094 --> 00:33:02,431
Those combination codes, you didn't
know what half of them even meant.

430
00:33:02,598 --> 00:33:05,225
You threw them in there cocky
and half-assed.

431
00:33:05,392 --> 00:33:07,853
- You never gave him a chance.
- He wasn't that good.

432
00:33:08,020 --> 00:33:09,521
Noisy Boy was a great robot.

433
00:33:09,688 --> 00:33:12,441
Was. Was a great robot
back in the League, back in the day.

434
00:33:12,608 --> 00:33:16,570
But look around you. This place is
where once great robots go to die.

435
00:33:16,737 --> 00:33:18,113
So throw him away.

436
00:33:18,280 --> 00:33:21,366
That's what you do, right?
Anything you don't need you throw away.

437
00:33:23,535 --> 00:33:24,620
Wow.

438
00:33:27,039 --> 00:33:28,373
It's been a long night.

439
00:33:28,540 --> 00:33:31,180
If you want to sleep indoors tonight,
shut up and get in the truck.

440
00:33:31,460 --> 00:33:33,712
Don't look at me like that way.
Get in the truck!

441
00:34:02,491 --> 00:34:04,034
They gave me 400 for his head.

442
00:34:21,927 --> 00:34:24,262
You stay put.
I'm going to look for parts.

443
00:34:24,429 --> 00:34:27,432
I'm coming with you.
That drink has my heart pounding.

444
00:34:27,599 --> 00:34:29,759
If I sit in this truck by myself,
my head will explode.

445
00:34:29,893 --> 00:34:31,353
Whatever. Just keep up.

446
00:34:42,698 --> 00:34:44,366
Crap.

447
00:34:44,533 --> 00:34:45,867
Stay back.

448
00:34:57,713 --> 00:34:59,256
All right, keep up.

449
00:35:00,882 --> 00:35:03,442
These searchlights are automated,
but you got to time them right,

450
00:35:03,593 --> 00:35:04,678
so stay close.

451
00:35:08,390 --> 00:35:09,474
It's all right.

452
00:35:10,642 --> 00:35:12,019
Come on, come on.

453
00:35:13,437 --> 00:35:15,397
- We're going to get caught.
- Come on.

454
00:35:16,940 --> 00:35:19,151
Easy, easy. Easy, easy.

455
00:35:19,317 --> 00:35:22,571
Quick, quick. Down in here! Go, go, go!

456
00:35:25,574 --> 00:35:28,368
Robots are on the east side.
We got to be quick in here.

457
00:35:30,746 --> 00:35:33,707
Once we're through here,
there's no more searchlights. Quick! Go!

458
00:35:50,724 --> 00:35:52,476
- Here it is.
- What are we looking for?

459
00:35:52,642 --> 00:35:55,145
Anything I could use
to put a fighting bot together.

460
00:35:55,312 --> 00:35:57,314
- Hey, look.
- What?

461
00:35:59,524 --> 00:36:01,485
It's so small.

462
00:36:01,651 --> 00:36:03,278
Yeah. That's before your time.

463
00:36:03,445 --> 00:36:06,531
That's a Generation One,
the very first fighting bot.

464
00:36:06,698 --> 00:36:09,951
They wanted them to look like us.
The more human, the better.

465
00:36:10,118 --> 00:36:12,788
Crazy how quick everything changed.
Put that in the cart.

466
00:36:12,954 --> 00:36:16,124
- What changed?
- A good question. Human boxing.

467
00:36:16,291 --> 00:36:18,168
- It just faded.
- Why?

468
00:36:19,086 --> 00:36:23,632
Because the money moved on.
People wanted more carnage, more show.

469
00:36:23,799 --> 00:36:26,843
You had the whole Brazilian underground,
the Gracies, the Machados,

470
00:36:27,010 --> 00:36:30,180
jiu-jitsu, Muay Thai,
and a thousand styles in between.

471
00:36:30,347 --> 00:36:31,723
Full-on ground-and-pound.

472
00:36:31,890 --> 00:36:33,141
- Look at this.
- What's that?

473
00:36:33,308 --> 00:36:34,476
I don't know.

474
00:36:34,643 --> 00:36:35,977
Not bad. Good spot.

475
00:36:36,853 --> 00:36:39,147
You still had human fighters,
human bodies,

476
00:36:39,314 --> 00:36:41,525
so you couldn't give the people
what they really wanted:

477
00:36:41,691 --> 00:36:43,985
true, no-holds-barred violence.

478
00:36:46,655 --> 00:36:48,824
The next logical step,

479
00:36:48,990 --> 00:36:52,119
get the humans out of there
and let the machines kill each other.

480
00:36:53,161 --> 00:36:54,496
Do you miss it?

481
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:59,501
- Boxing. Do you miss it?
- Careful.

482
00:36:59,668 --> 00:37:01,044
What? I want to know.

483
00:37:01,211 --> 00:37:03,004
Careful, you're on a cliff.

484
00:37:07,717 --> 00:37:10,595
That's a long way down.
If you fell, you'd definitely...

485
00:37:19,938 --> 00:37:22,357
Charlie, help me!

486
00:37:46,548 --> 00:37:48,049
Charlie!

487
00:37:49,259 --> 00:37:52,179
- Charlie!
- Max! Max!

488
00:37:54,097 --> 00:37:55,098
Max!

489
00:37:58,059 --> 00:38:01,563
- Try not to move!
- I'm on some sort of robot arm.

490
00:38:01,730 --> 00:38:05,734
Wait! Just easy, easy.
Give me your hand. Nice and easy.

491
00:38:05,901 --> 00:38:10,238
Very slowly. Good. Don't look down.
Look at me. Look at me.

492
00:38:10,405 --> 00:38:14,242
That's it! I've got you!
You don't have to be soared. I got you!

493
00:38:14,409 --> 00:38:16,745
- It's so far!
- It's OK. I got you.

494
00:38:16,912 --> 00:38:19,247
Give me your other hand. Nice and slow.

495
00:38:19,915 --> 00:38:24,836
Just give me your other hand very
slowly. Reach back. Come on. Reach!

496
00:38:25,003 --> 00:38:27,505
Look at me.
We're going to do this together.

497
00:38:27,672 --> 00:38:30,926
You and me. Just look at me. That's it.

498
00:38:32,010 --> 00:38:35,347
One... two... three!

499
00:38:37,432 --> 00:38:42,771
That's it. I got you!
I got you. I got you. I got you.

500
00:38:49,444 --> 00:38:51,613
You're safe. You're safe.

501
00:38:55,575 --> 00:38:56,910
All right, I got you.

502
00:38:57,077 --> 00:38:58,453
- You all right?
- Yeah.

503
00:38:58,620 --> 00:39:00,997
Come here. Easy. Easy.

504
00:39:02,832 --> 00:39:04,292
You all right?

505
00:39:04,459 --> 00:39:05,794
- You all right?
- Yeah.

506
00:39:05,961 --> 00:39:07,837
I told you it was dangerous.

507
00:39:08,630 --> 00:39:10,298
Careful. We're still on the edge here.

508
00:39:23,186 --> 00:39:26,314
Charlie, I think
there's a whole robot in there.

509
00:39:26,481 --> 00:39:27,774
So what? Let's go. Come on.

510
00:39:28,566 --> 00:39:30,443
I'm taking him with me.
He saved my life.

511
00:39:30,610 --> 00:39:33,989
He did not save your life.
I saved your life. Let's go.

512
00:39:34,155 --> 00:39:37,117
Just bring the cart to the edge.
I'll use the winch to get him out.

513
00:39:37,284 --> 00:39:40,662
You want that piece of junk? You get
the cart yourself. I'm through here.

514
00:41:25,683 --> 00:41:27,394
This is what's left of Noisy Boy?

515
00:41:27,560 --> 00:41:28,560
That's it.

516
00:41:28,686 --> 00:41:31,398
His head does make a nice addition
to the front of the Crash Palace.

517
00:41:33,066 --> 00:41:35,610
- It's not funny.
- Let's get a robot, you and me.

518
00:41:35,777 --> 00:41:38,905
Good idea. You're broke.
I'm almost there myself.

519
00:41:39,072 --> 00:41:41,825
- You destroyed the best shot you had.
- We'll put one together.

520
00:41:41,991 --> 00:41:43,427
You're brilliant at this.
There's good stuff here.

521
00:41:43,451 --> 00:41:45,578
- There's nothing here.
- There is. Look.

522
00:41:45,745 --> 00:41:48,623
All yourjunk is... it's junk.

523
00:41:50,458 --> 00:41:52,877
You're not even in the game anymore.

524
00:41:53,044 --> 00:41:54,963
- It's all garbage.
- I heard you. It's garbage.

525
00:41:55,130 --> 00:41:56,798
Don't get loud with me.

526
00:41:56,965 --> 00:41:58,943
- You're your problem.
- What's that supposed to mean?

527
00:41:58,967 --> 00:42:01,803
I have been here for you a long time.

528
00:42:01,970 --> 00:42:05,640
In the ring, out of the ring, and the
whole ugly spiral down, and I'm tired.

529
00:42:05,807 --> 00:42:09,811
My father invested everything he had
in your fight career. We loved...

530
00:42:11,479 --> 00:42:16,276
He loved you like family.
And this is his home.

531
00:42:16,943 --> 00:42:19,612
I'm just trying not to let it die.
That's my plan.

532
00:42:20,989 --> 00:42:22,323
What's yours?

533
00:42:34,169 --> 00:42:35,712
You're done, right?

534
00:42:35,879 --> 00:42:40,675
You're finally done?
Because I sure as hell am, Charlie.

535
00:42:41,843 --> 00:42:43,344
I got nothing left.

536
00:42:45,388 --> 00:42:46,389
All right.

537
00:42:48,892 --> 00:42:50,560
Maybe there's something here.

538
00:42:51,895 --> 00:42:55,732
This robot the kid brought in last
night. Would you look at it for me?

539
00:42:56,441 --> 00:42:57,442
Please?

540
00:43:06,367 --> 00:43:10,997
I've never seen anything like it before.
He's Generation Two, but barely.

541
00:43:11,164 --> 00:43:15,710
I found a power cell that fits him, and
I hooked him up to this old G-2 remote.

542
00:43:15,877 --> 00:43:18,004
You can move him around, but he's crap.

543
00:43:18,171 --> 00:43:21,049
Maybe I can get a sparring gig for him,
make a few hundred bucks.

544
00:43:21,216 --> 00:43:22,383
Stop.

545
00:43:22,550 --> 00:43:24,135
It's my robot!

546
00:43:24,302 --> 00:43:27,889
It took me half the night
dragging him out of there. He's mine.

547
00:43:28,056 --> 00:43:31,601
He's yours? Yeah. But the parts
we're putting in him are mine!

548
00:43:33,019 --> 00:43:36,356
You idiots should see if he powers up
before you fight over him.

549
00:43:36,523 --> 00:43:37,774
What happened to you?

550
00:43:56,668 --> 00:43:58,253
Watch out. Stay back.

551
00:44:16,563 --> 00:44:19,732
Looks like he's got a shadow function.
That's pretty rare.

552
00:44:20,608 --> 00:44:22,944
He can mime your movements
and store them in memory.

553
00:44:23,111 --> 00:44:25,905
- Is there anything here we could use?
- Not much.

554
00:44:26,072 --> 00:44:27,115
There's a bucket...

555
00:44:28,449 --> 00:44:30,535
There's a bucket
I use to wash the truck.

556
00:44:30,702 --> 00:44:33,580
Use it and clean him up.
He smells like crap.

557
00:44:33,746 --> 00:44:36,541
Wash yourself off, too,
while you're at it. You stink.

558
00:44:36,708 --> 00:44:39,877
I switched him to remote.
It's pretty basic.

559
00:44:40,044 --> 00:44:42,422
Just use the toggles here
to steer him and walk him.

560
00:44:43,131 --> 00:44:45,925
- You play video games, right?
- Of course.

561
00:44:46,092 --> 00:44:48,803
Same idea, only this one's
a thousand-pound robot.

562
00:44:49,512 --> 00:44:50,513
Cool.

563
00:45:24,922 --> 00:45:26,257
"Atom."

564
00:45:33,681 --> 00:45:36,976
His name is Atom.
Can we get him a fight?

565
00:45:37,143 --> 00:45:38,579
I don't think he was
ever a boxing robot.

566
00:45:38,603 --> 00:45:42,649
He's a G-2, built in early 2014.
He was a sparring bot.

567
00:45:42,815 --> 00:45:44,209
They must have built robots
like this one

568
00:45:44,233 --> 00:45:46,433
that could mirror the fighting style
of any other robot.

569
00:45:46,486 --> 00:45:48,613
OK, so can we get him a fight?

570
00:45:48,780 --> 00:45:51,366
Are you not listening?
He's a sparring bot.

571
00:45:51,532 --> 00:45:54,261
Built to take a lot of hits, but never
dishing out any real punishment.

572
00:45:54,285 --> 00:45:55,885
You could always sell him off for parts.

573
00:45:56,037 --> 00:45:59,415
- Can't you get him a fight?
- "Why can't you get him a fight?"

574
00:45:59,582 --> 00:46:01,334
God, you don't quit, do you?

575
00:46:01,501 --> 00:46:04,379
You want me to put him in some
bottom-rung scrap-fest to the death?

576
00:46:04,545 --> 00:46:07,382
I saw how scared you were
at Crash Palace.

577
00:46:07,548 --> 00:46:11,719
The places that would let you fight this
robot would make you pee your pants.

578
00:46:11,886 --> 00:46:14,222
Excellent. Get him a fight.

579
00:46:20,395 --> 00:46:21,396
Stubborn kid.

580
00:46:21,562 --> 00:46:23,398
Surprise, surprise.

581
00:47:04,689 --> 00:47:06,023
Let's take a walk.

582
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:17,178
Can you understand me?

583
00:48:25,102 --> 00:48:28,272
Don't worry. Your secret's safe with me.

584
00:48:53,506 --> 00:48:55,091
You've known Charlie a long time.

585
00:48:56,217 --> 00:48:59,554
Too long.
We both kind of grew up in this gym.

586
00:49:01,472 --> 00:49:02,849
My dad, he trained him.

587
00:49:04,225 --> 00:49:06,686
That's them. That's Charlie.

588
00:49:09,188 --> 00:49:11,107
- What was he like?
- As a boxer?

589
00:49:11,274 --> 00:49:13,526
- As anything.
- He was something.

590
00:49:13,693 --> 00:49:17,280
He was lean, tough.

591
00:49:17,446 --> 00:49:19,282
No quit, no fear.

592
00:49:23,828 --> 00:49:25,830
Come here. I want to show you something.

593
00:49:27,498 --> 00:49:31,669
I have this newspaper article
from Phoenix 2007

594
00:49:31,836 --> 00:49:35,548
when Charlie fought Nico Tandy,
the top contender.

595
00:49:35,715 --> 00:49:37,091
You were at the Nico Tandy fight?

596
00:49:37,258 --> 00:49:41,220
I was. Charlie was supposed to be
a warm-up fight, an easy win.

597
00:49:41,387 --> 00:49:44,682
Nico wasn't even supposed
to break a sweat, but...

598
00:49:45,433 --> 00:49:50,271
nobody told Charlie that, so he
just kept coming and coming at him.

599
00:49:50,438 --> 00:49:51,772
Check this out.

600
00:49:54,901 --> 00:49:55,943
That's Charlie.

601
00:49:57,862 --> 00:50:00,448
First, Nico couldn't believe
the balls on this nobody.

602
00:50:00,615 --> 00:50:05,202
But Charlie kept coming,
and that's when Nico looked scared.

603
00:50:05,369 --> 00:50:07,121
- Really?
- Really.

604
00:50:07,288 --> 00:50:08,956
He was toying with Nico.

605
00:50:09,123 --> 00:50:11,709
The top contender,
number two in the world,

606
00:50:11,876 --> 00:50:13,961
and Charlie was dancing with him.

607
00:50:15,671 --> 00:50:18,716
Charlie was floating
inches off the canvas that night.

608
00:50:18,883 --> 00:50:21,719
He was like a ghost.
Nico couldn't even see him.

609
00:50:23,095 --> 00:50:24,472
I could.

610
00:50:27,141 --> 00:50:28,476
He was beautiful.

611
00:50:29,644 --> 00:50:30,978
He was beautiful.

612
00:50:33,773 --> 00:50:36,567
So what happened?
Did Charlie beat Nico Tandy?

613
00:50:36,734 --> 00:50:40,404
No, Nico Tandy put me on my ass
in the 12th round. Twice.

614
00:50:40,571 --> 00:50:42,365
Second time for good. Lights out.

615
00:50:42,531 --> 00:50:43,866
You were ahead on the scorecards

616
00:50:44,033 --> 00:50:46,160
- going into the 12th round.
- Nico Tandy rung my bell

617
00:50:46,327 --> 00:50:49,163
and went on to be the undefeated
world champ for the next three years.

618
00:50:49,330 --> 00:50:51,332
- He knocked you out?
- Yeah. So did a lot of guys.

619
00:50:51,499 --> 00:50:52,899
You knocked a lot of guys out, too.

620
00:50:53,000 --> 00:50:57,338
- 24 and 19. It's not exactly a career.
- But every fight a knockout.

621
00:50:57,505 --> 00:50:59,025
- Yeah.
- Win or lose, fight's not over

622
00:50:59,090 --> 00:51:00,692
- till someone's on the mat.
- Till someone's on the mat.

623
00:51:00,716 --> 00:51:03,316
- Your old man taught me that.
- Damn straight he taught you that.

624
00:51:03,344 --> 00:51:05,513
- Who else did you fight?
- Go get your stuff together.

625
00:51:05,680 --> 00:51:07,515
I don't need to.
Did you fight for the title?

626
00:51:07,682 --> 00:51:11,102
Yeah, you do. We leave in an hour. Go.

627
00:51:11,268 --> 00:51:12,979
Wow. Here.

628
00:51:15,189 --> 00:51:16,315
Keep it.

629
00:51:17,566 --> 00:51:20,069
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

630
00:51:24,740 --> 00:51:26,450
I like that kid.

631
00:51:27,368 --> 00:51:28,703
He likes you.

632
00:51:33,749 --> 00:51:37,169
- What I said yesterday was...
- No, nothing more to say.

633
00:51:39,046 --> 00:51:40,423
I'm heading off to Atlanta tonight

634
00:51:40,589 --> 00:51:43,801
to see if I can get a partner
or raise money to get a new bot.

635
00:51:45,011 --> 00:51:48,889
That's what you wanted, right? Me gone?

636
00:51:53,060 --> 00:51:55,396
Yeah, that's what I wanted.

637
00:52:03,904 --> 00:52:04,905
OK.

638
00:52:40,941 --> 00:52:42,109
Look.

639
00:52:49,200 --> 00:52:51,952
The champ is here. Zeus is here.

640
00:52:52,119 --> 00:52:53,621
Yeah.

641
00:52:55,748 --> 00:53:01,128
<i>Zeus! No one has ever gone two rounds
with this monster. Two rounds!</i>

642
00:53:01,295 --> 00:53:04,465
<i>The champ puts his Real Steel world
championship belt on the line tonight.</i>

643
00:53:04,632 --> 00:53:06,592
<i>He just may have a real fight
on his hands.</i>

644
00:53:06,759 --> 00:53:12,098
<i>Zeus, greatest robot boxer of all time.
Ever. End of story. Good night!</i>

645
00:53:12,932 --> 00:53:15,434
- So cool. It's so cool.
- What?

646
00:53:18,604 --> 00:53:19,605
Come on.

647
00:53:22,483 --> 00:53:24,527
Listen up. I got to go find Finn.

648
00:53:24,693 --> 00:53:26,445
I want you to stay in this area.

649
00:53:27,738 --> 00:53:30,574
Out of the way. Champ coming through.
Zeus coming through.

650
00:53:30,741 --> 00:53:32,243
Move, move. Champ coming through.

651
00:53:44,505 --> 00:53:47,675
Farra Lemkova, daughter behind
the father/daughter Zeus team.

652
00:53:47,842 --> 00:53:51,345
They say your father's the money
and you are the mind behind Zeus.

653
00:53:52,012 --> 00:53:53,347
You're very kind,

654
00:53:53,514 --> 00:53:57,393
but I assure you, the mind behind Zeus
belongs to the great Tak Mashido.

655
00:53:58,811 --> 00:54:02,189
What did it take to lure
the reclusive genius, former boy wonder

656
00:54:02,356 --> 00:54:05,526
and arguably the most important
bot designer in the history of the sport

657
00:54:05,693 --> 00:54:07,194
out of retirement?

658
00:54:08,070 --> 00:54:10,489
Why don't you ask him yourself?

659
00:54:15,369 --> 00:54:17,997
Is this Tak Mashido's greatest creation?

660
00:54:19,540 --> 00:54:23,586
Zeus is autonomous
and constantly evolving during a fight.

661
00:54:23,752 --> 00:54:25,754
With his adaptive operating system,

662
00:54:25,921 --> 00:54:30,885
he recognises patterns and rewrites
his fight code instantaneously.

663
00:54:32,386 --> 00:54:35,472
For myself and Joe Six-pack out there,
are you saying that Zeus...?

664
00:54:35,639 --> 00:54:39,935
I'm saying that no matter
what happens in that ring...

665
00:54:40,811 --> 00:54:44,231
the result of any fight is inevitable.

666
00:54:45,399 --> 00:54:46,942
What Zeus sees...

667
00:54:48,444 --> 00:54:49,778
he kills.

668
00:54:51,322 --> 00:54:52,990
Sweet.

669
00:55:22,186 --> 00:55:23,580
I'm never going into business with you.

670
00:55:23,604 --> 00:55:24,897
I just need a break here.

671
00:55:25,064 --> 00:55:27,834
You got that old bot truck out there.
You always got something in there.

672
00:55:27,858 --> 00:55:30,319
I got an old sparring bot,
ain't worth the paint left on it.

673
00:55:30,486 --> 00:55:32,071
What am I supposed to do with that?

674
00:55:32,238 --> 00:55:34,907
The Zoo. Take him to the Zoo.
They fight there tomorrow.

675
00:55:35,074 --> 00:55:37,034
Even I wouldn't be caught dead
at the Zoo.

676
00:55:37,201 --> 00:55:39,036
I just need a little loan.

677
00:55:40,454 --> 00:55:41,622
What?

678
00:55:42,623 --> 00:55:44,458
- You're serious, Charlie?
- A loan.

679
00:55:44,625 --> 00:55:46,794
Couple hundred. Few hundred.
Whatever you got.

680
00:55:47,920 --> 00:55:49,338
You know I'm good for it.

681
00:55:49,505 --> 00:55:53,300
I know you, and as much
as I like you, dude...

682
00:55:54,343 --> 00:55:56,136
you're a bad bet, brother.

683
00:56:00,015 --> 00:56:01,016
Right, yeah.

684
00:56:21,245 --> 00:56:23,622
Did you see that?
That's what's left of Axelrod.

685
00:56:23,789 --> 00:56:25,541
Where you been? I told you to stay put.

686
00:56:25,708 --> 00:56:28,002
You should have seen him.
Zeus was, like, amazing!

687
00:56:28,168 --> 00:56:30,129
- Amazing, huh?
- Unbelievable, yeah.

688
00:56:30,296 --> 00:56:34,383
He was just peppering Axelrod with
punches, but so fast. It was incredible.

689
00:56:34,550 --> 00:56:38,095
Axelrod didn't even land a punch.
He didn't even survive the first round.

690
00:56:38,262 --> 00:56:39,489
Is that what you think boxing is?

691
00:56:39,513 --> 00:56:41,658
Zeus beating up some piece of steel
that they feed him?

692
00:56:41,682 --> 00:56:44,518
Axelrod's not just some piece of steel.
And that is what boxing is now.

693
00:56:44,685 --> 00:56:47,229
Deal with it.
And I love it, and I'm in it now.

694
00:56:47,396 --> 00:56:50,399
You're in it now, are you?
You and your G-2 sparring bot?

695
00:56:50,566 --> 00:56:53,986
He's more than that.
If you'd get us a fight, you'd see.

696
00:56:54,153 --> 00:56:57,114
You're in luck, kid.
There's a lovely place called the Zoo.

697
00:56:57,281 --> 00:56:58,991
Tomorrow afternoon,
you'll get your fight.

698
00:56:59,158 --> 00:57:01,410
- Great.
- And it will be the end.

699
00:57:02,536 --> 00:57:04,872
I told you I hate hamburgers!

700
00:57:08,709 --> 00:57:09,877
It's a burrito!

701
00:57:18,927 --> 00:57:20,429
Right uppercut.

702
00:57:23,140 --> 00:57:24,892
Left uppercut.

703
00:57:27,603 --> 00:57:31,440
Bend your knees.
Rise up with both hands.

704
00:57:33,400 --> 00:57:37,738
Again. Bend your knees.
Rise up with both hands.

705
00:57:37,905 --> 00:57:40,157
You been up all night?

706
00:57:40,324 --> 00:57:41,742
Yeah. I cleaned him up.

707
00:57:41,909 --> 00:57:45,245
I'm using shadow mode to program some
fight moves and sync them to the remote.

708
00:57:45,412 --> 00:57:48,624
Yeah. I saw that double-up punch
you were showing him.

709
00:57:48,791 --> 00:57:51,043
That's lethal stuff.

710
00:57:51,210 --> 00:57:52,378
Let's do this.

711
00:57:54,088 --> 00:57:55,464
Let's do breakfast first.

712
00:58:32,835 --> 00:58:34,835
You know you're bringing him
home in pieces, right?

713
00:58:36,964 --> 00:58:38,132
We'll see.

714
00:58:46,348 --> 00:58:49,226
- Let me deal with this.
- Charlie Kenton. This is Max.

715
00:58:49,393 --> 00:58:51,145
Kingpin. Call me Kingpin.

716
00:58:51,311 --> 00:58:53,814
- All right, Kingpin, so...
- How much a round?

717
00:58:53,981 --> 00:58:55,524
We on a field trip?

718
00:58:57,818 --> 00:59:00,154
All right. He can fight my robot Metro.

719
00:59:00,320 --> 00:59:02,298
I'll give you a hundred bucks
for one two-minute round.

720
00:59:02,322 --> 00:59:03,532
- Take it.
- Three hundred.

721
00:59:03,699 --> 00:59:07,327
