01:17:57,832 --> 01:17:59,992
- and he's going to get his ass kicked.
- He's a boxer.

960
01:18:00,126 --> 01:18:02,461
We taught him to box.
You taught him to box!

961
01:18:03,170 --> 01:18:05,131
- That's worth something.
- I think it is, too.

962
01:18:05,298 --> 01:18:08,801
I think it's worth 200 grand.
Two hundred grand.

963
01:18:08,968 --> 01:18:11,929
We can go round and round this
all night long.

964
01:18:12,096 --> 01:18:13,389
Look at me.

965
01:18:14,682 --> 01:18:16,017
But it's not going to happen.

966
01:18:17,268 --> 01:18:18,603
I got a fight to get to.

967
01:18:33,159 --> 01:18:36,996
Ladies and gentlemen, tonight,

968
01:18:37,163 --> 01:18:41,834
<i>the march towards
the Real Steel Championship</i>

969
01:18:42,001 --> 01:18:45,046
<i>makes its way through Detroit's</i>

970
01:18:45,212 --> 01:18:49,258
Virgin America Spectrum!

971
01:18:53,262 --> 01:18:57,683
Kicking off the evening,
in our first undercard,

972
01:18:57,850 --> 01:19:00,603
the two-headed tyrant,

973
01:19:00,770 --> 01:19:05,149
Twin Cities!

974
01:19:35,680 --> 01:19:40,768
Opposing Twin Cities,
in his first professional fight,

975
01:19:40,935 --> 01:19:44,522
hailing from parts unknown,

976
01:19:44,689 --> 01:19:46,315
Atom!

977
01:20:41,996 --> 01:20:43,456
- Nice work, boss.
- Thanks.

978
01:20:43,622 --> 01:20:45,502
- Did you switch him to fight mode?
- Of course.

979
01:20:45,624 --> 01:20:48,294
- This bot is tough to put down.
- Atom can do it.

980
01:20:49,295 --> 01:20:52,298
Look over there. You see those geeks
with the joysticks and consoles?

981
01:20:52,465 --> 01:20:54,265
They're controlling
everything their bot does.

982
01:20:54,300 --> 01:20:55,540
They're monitoring his systems,

983
01:20:55,634 --> 01:20:58,137
seeing what he sees,
stadium feeds of the fights.

984
01:20:58,304 --> 01:21:00,365
This is not like the underground
handheld remote bots

985
01:21:00,389 --> 01:21:02,451
we've been fighting.
This is the League. Stand on that.

986
01:21:02,475 --> 01:21:04,435
So what do we do?

987
01:21:05,144 --> 01:21:08,731
We fight smart, we be patient. And pray.

988
01:21:10,232 --> 01:21:11,984
Seriously, pray.

989
01:21:14,612 --> 01:21:15,613
Ready!

990
01:21:16,822 --> 01:21:18,616
- Ready!
- Hands up.

991
01:21:18,783 --> 01:21:20,993
Fighters ready! Fight!

992
01:21:24,789 --> 01:21:25,915
Engage-.

993
01:21:27,291 --> 01:21:32,379
Slip! Right! Lean back.
Right, left! Cover up!

994
01:21:35,633 --> 01:21:36,926
Duck! Left roundhouse!

995
01:21:39,762 --> 01:21:41,055
Damn it.

996
01:21:48,479 --> 01:21:52,066
Lean left! Lean right!
Cover up! Cover up!

997
01:21:52,233 --> 01:21:55,110
- What's going on in there?
- He's taking too many hits.

998
01:22:01,033 --> 01:22:02,284
Get your hands up!

999
01:22:05,204 --> 01:22:06,956
Get out of that corner! Move!

1000
01:22:10,042 --> 01:22:12,503
He's getting killed in there!
Tell him what to do!

1001
01:22:12,670 --> 01:22:15,381
That guy's got two heads, a foot
of reach on us, and no blind spot.

1002
01:22:15,548 --> 01:22:17,383
He's got to have a weakness. Find it!

1003
01:22:23,389 --> 01:22:24,598
Wait, wait, wait.

1004
01:22:25,307 --> 01:22:28,143
Right shoulder, right shoulder,
right shoulder! He's got a tell!

1005
01:22:28,310 --> 01:22:30,997
He's got a hitch in his shoulder
every time he throws that right bomb!

1006
01:22:31,021 --> 01:22:33,148
We got him!
See? Here it comes again!

1007
01:22:33,315 --> 01:22:35,985
Duck! Spin!
Slide left! Roundhouse! One, two!

1008
01:22:36,151 --> 01:22:39,405
Backstep. Backstep.
Backstep. Lean right.

1009
01:22:39,572 --> 01:22:41,574
Come on, Charlie! Get in there!

1010
01:22:41,740 --> 01:22:44,300
Got to get in close where
he can't use that size and reach on us!

1011
01:22:44,368 --> 01:22:47,538
Left to the body! Right to the body!
Left to the body!

1012
01:22:47,705 --> 01:22:49,039
Yeah, it's working!

1013
01:22:49,206 --> 01:22:51,000
Stay downstairs! Left, right, left!

1014
01:22:52,585 --> 01:22:55,421
- These program modes aren't working.
- Left! Right hook, slip!

1015
01:22:55,588 --> 01:22:59,091
Right uppercut! Left uppercut!
Duck left. Counter right!

1016
01:22:59,258 --> 01:23:01,927
- Get him, Atom!
- Here comes the Charlie Special.

1017
01:23:02,094 --> 01:23:05,014
Three-punch combo to the body!
Out! In! Counter!

1018
01:23:05,180 --> 01:23:07,057
- Two-one-two!
- Two-one-two.

1019
01:23:07,224 --> 01:23:08,684
Stay on him! Lunging right!

1020
01:23:11,604 --> 01:23:14,189
Don't let him go. Right to the body!
Straight right to the head!

1021
01:23:19,194 --> 01:23:20,779
We got a systems crash!

1022
01:23:20,946 --> 01:23:22,281
Get him, Atom!

1023
01:23:25,576 --> 01:23:26,869
This is not happening, man.

1024
01:23:27,036 --> 01:23:29,288
- Put him away, Charlie!
- Spin left!

1025
01:23:30,289 --> 01:23:31,624
Spin right!

1026
01:23:33,876 --> 01:23:34,877
Finish him!

1027
01:23:35,044 --> 01:23:37,087
- Do it!
- Right uppercut!

1028
01:23:47,348 --> 01:23:48,474
He's down!

1029
01:23:49,475 --> 01:23:52,811
One! Two! Three!

1030
01:23:52,978 --> 01:23:55,814
Four! Five! Six!

1031
01:23:55,981 --> 01:23:57,900
We got him. Stay down!

1032
01:24:00,235 --> 01:24:01,820
He's out! He's out!

1033
01:24:07,826 --> 01:24:08,869
Yeah!

1034
01:24:11,872 --> 01:24:13,666
Corner!

1035
01:24:13,832 --> 01:24:16,794
Corner! Corner.

1036
01:24:18,420 --> 01:24:19,672
Victory!

1037
01:24:20,965 --> 01:24:25,052
In a time of one minute, 47 seconds

1038
01:24:25,219 --> 01:24:27,680
of the first round,

1039
01:24:27,846 --> 01:24:29,473
Atom has defeat...

1040
01:24:30,641 --> 01:24:33,352
I want to thank everyone
for coming out tonight!

1041
01:24:36,021 --> 01:24:40,150
Our little bot from the junkyard
got a shot at a League fight.

1042
01:24:40,317 --> 01:24:41,652
How about that?

1043
01:24:42,903 --> 01:24:47,491
And the last thing I want to say
to a special girl who won't be named,

1044
01:24:47,658 --> 01:24:49,451
Farra Lemkova.

1045
01:24:53,872 --> 01:24:57,543
That instead of buying my robot, using
your money to control this sport...

1046
01:24:57,710 --> 01:24:59,461
- That's it!
- I'm not done.

1047
01:24:59,628 --> 01:25:02,172
Why not give the littlest guy
the biggest shot?

1048
01:25:02,840 --> 01:25:06,677
Because I bet if you give him a shot,
he'll surprise you!

1049
01:25:06,844 --> 01:25:08,324
Wouldn't you like to see a little guy

1050
01:25:08,429 --> 01:25:10,431
get a shot at the
Real Steel Championship?

1051
01:25:14,518 --> 01:25:17,980
I challenge Zeus to a fight.

1052
01:25:20,065 --> 01:25:24,069
Any time, any place, anywhere!

1053
01:25:24,236 --> 01:25:27,197
You name it! We will be there!

1054
01:25:34,997 --> 01:25:36,915
I'm going to get us that fight!

1055
01:25:40,836 --> 01:25:43,839
Atom, Atom, Atom...

1056
01:25:56,769 --> 01:25:59,021
That was a ballsy move,
you challenging Zeus like that.

1057
01:25:59,188 --> 01:26:00,522
That's one thing to call it.

1058
01:26:00,689 --> 01:26:02,249
A lot of people would like to see that.

1059
01:26:02,274 --> 01:26:05,110
- You're damn right they would.
- You listening to this kid? Jeez!

1060
01:26:05,277 --> 01:26:07,112
- Good fight, fellas.
- Thanks, man.

1061
01:26:07,279 --> 01:26:09,073
- Look at this. Let's celebrate.
- Yeah.

1062
01:26:09,239 --> 01:26:12,326
- All right, 70-30, right?
- Yeah, 70 for me and 30 for you.

1063
01:26:12,493 --> 01:26:14,119
- That's so right.
- That's very funny.

1064
01:26:14,286 --> 01:26:18,290
- I told you we shouldn't have sold him.
- OK. No, no, no.

1065
01:26:18,457 --> 01:26:22,628
I remember now. Who's right?
Say who's right. Say "Max is right."

1066
01:26:22,795 --> 01:26:24,713
All right, all right. All right.

1067
01:26:24,880 --> 01:26:28,383
- We're a good team.
- No, no. Max is right.

1068
01:26:28,717 --> 01:26:31,011
That was unbelievable.
Thank you, Twin Cities.

1069
01:26:33,388 --> 01:26:34,932
- We set?
- Yeah.

1070
01:26:35,099 --> 01:26:37,267
- Let's do it.
- Charlie boy.

1071
01:26:38,268 --> 01:26:41,563
- Ricky, I was just going to call you.
- Oh, yeah.

1072
01:26:41,730 --> 01:26:44,525
I actually really was going to call you.

1073
01:26:44,733 --> 01:26:46,485
Don't worry about that.

1074
01:26:46,652 --> 01:26:48,654
That was a heck of a fight.

1075
01:26:48,821 --> 01:26:51,115
Congratulations to both of you.
That was good.

1076
01:26:51,281 --> 01:26:54,076
It was an amazing fight.
That was a great job, young man.

1077
01:26:55,077 --> 01:26:56,411
- Come on, man.
- What?

1078
01:26:56,578 --> 01:27:00,666
- You serious?
- You thought I was joking

1079
01:27:00,833 --> 01:27:02,769
when I said I'd beat you
within an inch of your life?

1080
01:27:02,793 --> 01:27:05,838
He thought that was a joke.
It wasn't a joke.

1081
01:27:06,004 --> 01:27:10,175
I got a kid here. And I have your money.
We don't have a problem.

1082
01:27:10,342 --> 01:27:13,011
I'm sure you do,

1083
01:27:13,178 --> 01:27:16,181
but I think we know it's about
much more than money, don't we?

1084
01:27:16,348 --> 01:27:21,520
All right. What do you want?
You want 25, 30? You want 30 grand?

1085
01:27:21,687 --> 01:27:23,487
- I got the money in cash here.
- Yeah, right.

1086
01:27:23,522 --> 01:27:26,650
Let's go! Max, go! Go, go! Run!

1087
01:27:26,817 --> 01:27:30,154
- Run! Come on. Keep up, keep up!
- Get him now!

1088
01:27:30,320 --> 01:27:31,572
Run! Come on!

1089
01:27:33,490 --> 01:27:35,200
Get off him! Get off him!

1090
01:27:38,537 --> 01:27:39,538
Come here!

1091
01:27:44,001 --> 01:27:45,043
Hey, Ricky.

1092
01:27:45,210 --> 01:27:46,770
That's his money!
Leave him out of this!

1093
01:27:59,224 --> 01:28:01,143
Stop!

1094
01:28:03,562 --> 01:28:04,897
Stop!

1095
01:28:05,063 --> 01:28:08,567
Take all his money. Take it all.

1096
01:28:11,236 --> 01:28:13,614
Your friend's a real dirtbag, kid.

1097
01:28:13,780 --> 01:28:15,365
He's my father!

1098
01:28:17,576 --> 01:28:22,289
Well. Looks like a little less
than an inch of your life.

1099
01:28:22,456 --> 01:28:25,250
Well, buddy, that will teach him.

1100
01:28:30,839 --> 01:28:33,759
Just like old times, Charlie boy!

1101
01:28:33,926 --> 01:28:35,177
Let's go, boys.

1102
01:29:01,036 --> 01:29:05,290
I'm sorry, Max. I'm sorry. Sorry.

1103
01:29:45,831 --> 01:29:47,624
- What are we doing here?
- Max, just...

1104
01:29:47,791 --> 01:29:50,836
Is it Farra? She called you, didn't she?
We're going to get the Zeus fight.

1105
01:29:51,003 --> 01:29:55,173
It's not the Zeus people. I've been
thinking about all this, and...

1106
01:29:57,259 --> 01:29:58,343
Max!

1107
01:30:08,020 --> 01:30:09,771
It's so good to see you.

1108
01:30:09,938 --> 01:30:12,418
- What is she doing here?
- It's better if you go with her now.

1109
01:30:12,566 --> 01:30:14,651
We get beat up,
so you call her to come and get me?

1110
01:30:14,818 --> 01:30:16,754
He's been beat up. I told you
he couldn't take care of him!

1111
01:30:16,778 --> 01:30:19,531
Yeah. I called her.
Look at us. We're a mess.

1112
01:30:19,698 --> 01:30:21,700
We're fine. She can leave!

1113
01:30:21,867 --> 01:30:24,870
Atom's fighting good.
We can make the money back.

1114
01:30:25,620 --> 01:30:27,497
Charlie, please.

1115
01:30:28,540 --> 01:30:29,624
Just...

1116
01:30:32,544 --> 01:30:35,088
Charlie, we're doing so good.

1117
01:30:37,049 --> 01:30:38,967
Charlie, please, no.

1118
01:30:40,385 --> 01:30:42,888
Don't. Don't. Don't.

1119
01:30:43,930 --> 01:30:46,850
Please. Please.

1120
01:30:51,438 --> 01:30:54,566
Trust me, kid.
It's better this way, all right?

1121
01:30:55,400 --> 01:30:58,153
I know you think you know
what's right, but you don't.

1122
01:30:58,320 --> 01:30:59,905
You're too young. You don't know.

1123
01:31:00,072 --> 01:31:01,573
Look at me, trust me.

1124
01:31:01,740 --> 01:31:05,035
And legally she has custody,
so what can I do?

1125
01:31:05,994 --> 01:31:07,746
What can I do?

1126
01:31:23,095 --> 01:31:24,721
I don't want your money, Marvin.

1127
01:31:25,889 --> 01:31:27,933
Max, we have our own swimming pool

1128
01:31:28,100 --> 01:31:32,687
and we have a hot tub and a lot
of super fun toys to play with.

1129
01:31:32,854 --> 01:31:35,524
Do you want to play with them?
It's going to be fun.

1130
01:31:36,441 --> 01:31:37,776
What's going on?

1131
01:31:37,943 --> 01:31:40,612
He won't even talk to me,
so thanks for that, Charlie.

1132
01:31:41,696 --> 01:31:43,240
I'm going to wait in the car.

1133
01:31:45,867 --> 01:31:48,453
You don't want to talk, fine. I'll talk.

1134
01:31:48,620 --> 01:31:50,497
What do you want me to say? I'm sorry?

1135
01:31:50,664 --> 01:31:53,708
You knew from day one what this was.

1136
01:31:53,875 --> 01:31:55,669
You decided to take the ride.

1137
01:31:56,336 --> 01:32:00,132
You thought me, you,
and a little robot from the junk heap

1138
01:32:00,298 --> 01:32:02,717
were going to ride off into the sunset?

1139
01:32:04,803 --> 01:32:07,305
No, you forgot who I was!

1140
01:32:13,437 --> 01:32:14,729
You deserve better...

1141
01:32:16,314 --> 01:32:17,357
than me.

1142
01:32:21,862 --> 01:32:23,613
Will you say something, please?

1143
01:32:23,780 --> 01:32:26,241
I tried. What do you want from me?

1144
01:32:26,408 --> 01:32:28,118
I want you to fight for me.

1145
01:32:29,369 --> 01:32:31,163
That's all I ever wanted.

1146
01:34:36,413 --> 01:34:37,747
Don't ask.

1147
01:34:39,874 --> 01:34:41,418
So no Max.

1148
01:34:42,669 --> 01:34:46,423
It's better this way.
Marv and Debra have money. Max is set.

1149
01:34:46,590 --> 01:34:48,300
Did you not see the way
he looked at you?

1150
01:34:49,593 --> 01:34:51,678
That's the way I looked at my dad.

1151
01:34:51,845 --> 01:34:54,097
Even now I would give anything
to have that back.

1152
01:34:54,264 --> 01:34:58,310
Your dad was special.
He was in your corner from day one.

1153
01:34:59,311 --> 01:35:00,937
Me, come on. I blew it.

1154
01:35:02,897 --> 01:35:04,316
I blew it.

1155
01:35:05,233 --> 01:35:07,152
When Max was born I just...

1156
01:35:07,819 --> 01:35:09,237
freaked out.

1157
01:35:09,404 --> 01:35:11,656
But something
would have been better than nothing.

1158
01:35:11,823 --> 01:35:13,074
I wouldn't know where to start.

1159
01:35:13,241 --> 01:35:14,284
- Yeah, you do.
- I don't.

1160
01:35:14,451 --> 01:35:15,910
- You do.
- No.

1161
01:35:16,953 --> 01:35:17,996
You do.

1162
01:35:50,987 --> 01:35:52,030
<i>L</i> got to g0-

1163
01:35:55,158 --> 01:35:56,701
Twelve hundred miles for a kiss.

1164
01:35:58,203 --> 01:36:00,580
Worth it. Worth it.

1165
01:36:12,050 --> 01:36:13,593
Go get him, Charlie.

1166
01:36:16,971 --> 01:36:18,390
You sound like your dad.

1167
01:36:46,751 --> 01:36:50,463
Look, I know you think I abandoned you,

1168
01:36:50,630 --> 01:36:53,425
and I guess I did originally.

1169
01:36:53,591 --> 01:36:54,592
Then you sold me.

1170
01:36:55,260 --> 01:36:56,428
Charlie.

1171
01:36:57,512 --> 01:36:59,431
You have no business being here.

1172
01:36:59,597 --> 01:37:02,016
That's true.
You've got full custody. He's yours.

1173
01:37:02,183 --> 01:37:06,104
And I know I've done all kinds of wrong
by this kid, but if you'll let me...

1174
01:37:08,231 --> 01:37:10,233
I'd just like to do one thing right.

1175
01:37:13,194 --> 01:37:14,279
Right.

1176
01:37:15,905 --> 01:37:17,615
- Where were we?
- You sold me.

1177
01:37:17,782 --> 01:37:19,909
Right, yeah, that happened.

1178
01:37:20,076 --> 01:37:22,287
- Wait, what?
- Then we had our asses kicked.

1179
01:37:22,454 --> 01:37:24,622
And you slept on a shelf in a truck,
and it was awful.

1180
01:37:24,789 --> 01:37:26,416
- And dangerous.
- Really dangerous.

1181
01:37:26,583 --> 01:37:30,336
I mean, I know. God. I'm sorry.

1182
01:37:31,463 --> 01:37:34,466
That's why you came?
To say you're sorry?

1183
01:37:34,632 --> 01:37:36,968
No. I mean, yes. Yes.

1184
01:37:39,971 --> 01:37:43,641
But no. No, I came to tell you
that I heard you.

1185
01:37:44,642 --> 01:37:47,979
I got it.
I'm a little slow, but I got it.

1186
01:37:49,564 --> 01:37:53,026
I know you had a bum ride, and I
wasn't there and I should have been.

1187
01:37:54,360 --> 01:37:55,445
I should have been.

1188
01:37:56,696 --> 01:37:58,072
Your mom was...

1189
01:37:58,740 --> 01:38:00,492
She was cool, wasn't she?

1190
01:38:02,035 --> 01:38:03,119
She was.

1191
01:38:03,995 --> 01:38:05,330
She was the coolest.

1192
01:38:06,164 --> 01:38:08,750
Yeah, she was.

1193
01:38:11,669 --> 01:38:16,633
And I'm sorry about...
what happened with her.

1194
01:38:19,886 --> 01:38:22,680
And I can't get those years back, Max,

1195
01:38:22,847 --> 01:38:25,892
but I'm here right now...

1196
01:38:27,393 --> 01:38:30,688
and if you're up for it,
I'm ready to fight.

1197
01:38:44,702 --> 01:38:46,287
We got the Zeus fight.

1198
01:38:46,454 --> 01:38:47,664
What?

1199
01:38:47,831 --> 01:38:49,624
No, no, we didn't.

1200
01:38:50,542 --> 01:38:52,544
You got the Zeus fight.

1201
01:38:56,506 --> 01:38:58,383
So what do you say, Debra?

1202
01:38:58,550 --> 01:38:59,926
Can we do this one last thing?

1203
01:39:03,429 --> 01:39:05,932
- One night.
- It's all we need. Thank you.

1204
01:39:11,062 --> 01:39:14,774
We'll probably get our asses kicked,
but at least we'll go down swinging.

1205
01:39:15,692 --> 01:39:17,777
Yeah? What do you say?

1206
01:39:19,946 --> 01:39:24,367
<i>Welcome to New York's Bing Arena
and the Real Steel Championship Bout.</i>

1207
01:39:24,534 --> 01:39:26,870
<i>Tim, it's the fight
we never thought we'd see.</i>

1208
01:39:27,036 --> 01:39:29,247
<i>Zeus, the undefeated WRB champion,</i>

1209
01:39:29,414 --> 01:39:32,709
<i>against the underdog, rising star Atom.</i>

1210
01:39:32,876 --> 01:39:34,711
<i>The champ's handlers
have agreed to fight</i>

1211
01:39:34,878 --> 01:39:37,422
<i>outside the circle
of well-known League bots,</i>

1212
01:39:37,589 --> 01:39:41,718
<i>and have decided to give the people
a true David versus Goliath spectacle.</i>

1213
01:39:41,885 --> 01:39:45,263
Now, Tim, help me out on this.
Has the Zeus camp lost their mind?

1214
01:39:45,430 --> 01:39:47,098
The greatest robot boxer of all time

1215
01:39:47,265 --> 01:39:50,184
gives a shot at the belt
to a G-2 named Atom?

1216
01:39:50,351 --> 01:39:54,272
Well, Herb, if you ask Tak Mashido,
Team Zeus has lost their minds.

1217
01:39:54,439 --> 01:39:56,691
Now, he may look cool
as he enters the arena,

1218
01:39:56,858 --> 01:39:59,861
but he has made no bones
about his disdain for this matchup.

1219
01:40:00,028 --> 01:40:02,780
Our cameras tried to catch up
with him earlier this week.

1220
01:40:02,947 --> 01:40:05,950
Look at this clip. Mashido wouldn't
even stop to talk to the press,

1221
01:40:06,117 --> 01:40:09,287
<i>referring only to this fight
as an insult to his creation.</i>

1222
01:40:09,454 --> 01:40:13,249
Now, Max Kenton, Atom's trainer,
did more than just challenge Zeus.

1223
01:40:13,416 --> 01:40:14,626
He did so publicly.

1224
01:40:14,792 --> 01:40:18,379
The challenge went viral and created
a PR nightmare for the champ.

1225
01:40:18,546 --> 01:40:22,133
No argument there. And I think the Zeus
camp knows exactly what they're doing.

1226
01:40:22,300 --> 01:40:23,801
That they do. Come on.

1227
01:40:23,968 --> 01:40:26,971
Giving a shot at the belt
to a nobody from nowhere.

1228
01:40:27,138 --> 01:40:30,183
This "junkyard dog," if you will.
That's a marketing stunt.

1229
01:40:30,350 --> 01:40:33,102
And judging from this crowd,
that stunt is working.

1230
01:40:47,450 --> 01:40:48,826
We can't win, can we?

1231
01:40:49,953 --> 01:40:50,995
We'll see.

1232
01:40:55,291 --> 01:40:57,502
As the challenger
makes his way into the arena,

1233
01:40:57,669 --> 01:40:59,837
you can hear the surge of excitement.

1234
01:41:11,265 --> 01:41:14,644
Atom has arrived
onto the WRB scene with a vengeance,

1235
01:41:14,811 --> 01:41:17,522
using a style,
some would call it human-like,

1236
01:41:17,689 --> 01:41:20,108
that bot fighting has rarely seen.

1237
01:41:20,274 --> 01:41:22,527
Atom and his pint-size trainer
step into the ring

1238
01:41:22,694 --> 01:41:25,446
and the look on
Farra Lemkova's face says it all.

1239
01:41:25,613 --> 01:41:27,824
Welcome to the bigs, junior!

1240
01:41:27,991 --> 01:41:30,831
I'm giving one-to-five odds that Atom
don't make it out the first round.

1241
01:41:30,868 --> 01:41:32,203
Who wants some?

1242
01:41:33,037 --> 01:41:34,622
I'll take some of that action.

1243
01:41:34,789 --> 01:41:38,001
Hey, there!
I'll take some of that action.

1244
01:41:39,210 --> 01:41:42,213
How's it going... partner?

1245
01:41:42,380 --> 01:41:43,840
Partner?

1246
01:41:44,298 --> 01:41:47,468
That's great. How about a hundred K?
Is that funny?

1247
01:41:47,635 --> 01:41:50,221
Hundred K says Atom
doesn't see round two.

1248
01:41:50,388 --> 01:41:52,098
You carrying around
that kind of scratch?

1249
01:41:53,516 --> 01:41:55,727
- Yeah.
- Hundred K?

1250
01:41:56,394 --> 01:42:00,565
Tell you what.
Remember section 101, row C,

1251
01:42:00,732 --> 01:42:03,401
and you can bring me
my money right to my seat.

1252
01:42:03,568 --> 01:42:07,030
101, row C? Hundred K?

1253
01:42:07,739 --> 01:42:09,073
You heard me, homey.

1254
01:42:09,240 --> 01:42:10,992
- Homey?
- Right?

1255
01:42:11,159 --> 01:42:12,368
Homeboy!

1256
01:42:13,578 --> 01:42:15,955
All right. Peace out, posse.

1257
01:42:16,122 --> 01:42:17,457
Come on, sugar. Let's go.

1258
01:42:41,272 --> 01:42:43,983
- Never beaten.
- It's showtime!

1259
01:42:44,150 --> 01:42:46,277
Never threatened.

1260
01:42:46,444 --> 01:42:49,614
The king of the ring,

1261
01:42:49,781 --> 01:42:51,866
the ruler of robots!

1262
01:42:53,117 --> 01:42:58,289
Bow down to the mighty Zeus!

1263
01:43:24,065 --> 01:43:25,066
Oh, shit!

1264
01:43:31,614 --> 01:43:32,907
That was awesome.

1265
01:43:39,539 --> 01:43:40,706
Come on, let's go.

1266
01:43:47,505 --> 01:43:50,174
Ladies and gentlemen,

1267
01:43:50,341 --> 01:43:52,927
in a bout scheduled for five rounds

1268
01:43:53,094 --> 01:43:56,347
for the World Robot
Boxing Championship,

1269
01:43:56,514 --> 01:44:01,060
in the corner to my right,
the challenger, Atom!

1270
01:44:01,227 --> 01:44:02,353
Showboat!

1271
01:44:06,357 --> 01:44:08,818
And in the corner to my left,

1272
01:44:08,985 --> 01:44:11,988
the undeniable champion
of this universe

1273
01:44:12,155 --> 01:44:15,575
and any other universe known
or unknown,

1274
01:44:15,741 --> 01:44:20,037
the mighty Zeus!

1275
01:44:24,542 --> 01:44:28,713
And now, ladies and gentlemen,
are you ready

1276
01:44:28,880 --> 01:44:33,885
for Real Steel!

1277
01:44:36,846 --> 01:44:38,014
This is what it's all about!

1278
01:44:38,181 --> 01:44:42,101
There's the starting bell
and we are underway.

1279
01:44:42,268 --> 01:44:44,145
The bots emerge from their corners.

1280
01:44:45,062 --> 01:44:48,107
Zeus decks Atom, and he is already down.

1281
01:44:48,274 --> 01:44:49,400
On your feet!

1282
01:44:49,567 --> 01:44:52,111
Looks like we are in
for another Zeus clinic.

1283
01:44:54,530 --> 01:44:56,949
Referee Matt Geiger
coming in the ring to start the count.

1284
01:44:58,075 --> 01:44:59,118
Get up!

1285
01:45:00,703 --> 01:45:02,914
Push up! Stand up!

1286
01:45:03,998 --> 01:45:06,459
But look at this.
The little bot's back on his feet

1287
01:45:06,626 --> 01:45:09,212
to get a second blistering attack
from Zeus!

1288
01:45:09,378 --> 01:45:12,298
Atom is down for the second time
in less than ten seconds.

1289
01:45:12,465 --> 01:45:16,427
- He's too strong!
- That's my boy right there!

1290
01:45:18,429 --> 01:45:20,097
Get up and get in the game!

1291
01:45:20,264 --> 01:45:23,267
Come on! No, please Atom, get up!
Please!

1292
01:45:23,434 --> 01:45:26,062
Get up! Get up! Get up!

1293
01:45:27,605 --> 01:45:31,108
Once again,
the challenger finds his feet!

1294
01:45:31,609 --> 01:45:32,610
Lean back!

1295
01:45:32,777 --> 01:45:35,112
Atom's getting pummelled into the corner!

1296
01:45:35,279 --> 01:45:37,448
- Get out of there!
- Move!

1297
01:45:39,825 --> 01:45:41,869
A demolishing inside shot.

1298
01:45:42,036 --> 01:45:43,162
Get your hands up!

1299
01:45:45,248 --> 01:45:46,624
Hands up!

1300
01:45:47,625 --> 01:45:49,126
Crush that little can!

1301
01:45:49,293 --> 01:45:50,628
Get out of the corner!

1302
01:45:50,795 --> 01:45:54,131
Kenton desperately trying to command
his robot out of that suicide corner.

1303
01:45:59,053 --> 01:46:00,137
Get your feet under you!

1304
01:46:01,764 --> 01:46:03,808
Good night, sparring bot!

1305
01:46:03,975 --> 01:46:06,560
It might have taken Zeus a bit longer,
but he's done it again!

1306
01:46:06,727 --> 01:46:10,147
Atom is down for the third
and possibly final time tonight.

1307
01:46:10,314 --> 01:46:12,483
<i>_</i> Stand up!
" Two!

1308
01:46:12,650 --> 01:46:14,068
Three!

1309
01:46:14,235 --> 01:46:15,403
Atom, get UP!

1310
01:46:15,569 --> 01:46:17,655
- Get up, Atom.
- Get up, Atom.

1311
01:46:18,322 --> 01:46:21,075
- Six! Seven!
- Get up!

1312
01:46:21,242 --> 01:46:23,077
Eight! Nine!

1313
01:46:24,161 --> 01:46:28,541
I don't believe this! Against all odds,
this little bot is on his feet again.

1314
01:46:29,834 --> 01:46:30,876
Come on, Atom!

1315
01:46:34,088 --> 01:46:35,256
He can't survive this!

1316
01:46:39,051 --> 01:46:41,304
- Come on, Charlie!
- Right uppercut!

1317
01:46:42,596 --> 01:46:45,349
Atom has landed a punch!

1318
01:46:45,516 --> 01:46:50,521
Zeus is stunned as he reels back from
an uppercut that he never saw coming!

1319
01:46:50,688 --> 01:46:52,189
Advance!

1320
01:46:52,356 --> 01:46:53,691
Fade back, counter right!

1321
01:46:54,442 --> 01:46:55,609
Fade back, counter right!

1322
01:46:56,444 --> 01:47:00,865
Right cross! Right cross!
Right cross! Left hook!

1323
01:47:01,032 --> 01:47:03,909
- Let's go! Come on!
- Take him down!

1324
01:47:04,535 --> 01:47:06,579
For the first time in his dominant run,

1325
01:47:06,746 --> 01:47:10,541
Zeus has met a bot
who simply won't back down!

1326
01:47:12,376 --> 01:47:15,129
The crowd is going nuts!
Zeus gives it everything he's got

1327
01:47:15,296 --> 01:47:18,215
as we reach the last 15 seconds
of round one!

1328
01:47:18,382 --> 01:47:22,345
Zeus corners Atom,
going double duty with both fists!

1329
01:47:22,511 --> 01:47:25,431
Downtown, uptown,
as the clock winds down!

1330
01:47:25,598 --> 01:47:28,642
- Hands up, chin down.
- Stay low, stay low!

1331
01:47:32,355 --> 01:47:37,401
Only five seconds left, as here comes
that piston-packed right of the champ!

1332
01:47:38,819 --> 01:47:43,032
There's the bell! I don't believe it.
Somehow Atom has survived.

1333
01:47:43,199 --> 01:47:48,245
We will have a second round.
And the crowd here is thrilled!

1334
01:47:51,415 --> 01:47:54,502
He made it! Yeah! Corner!

1335
01:47:56,128 --> 01:47:59,924
We got to get out of here.
We got to get out of here now!

1336
01:48:02,718 --> 01:48:05,012
We got to go this way. Come on!

1337
01:48:10,518 --> 01:48:11,852
OK, you sit down.

1338
01:48:15,106 --> 01:48:17,691
- Let's go, homey.
- All right.

1339
01:48:17,858 --> 01:48:19,402
I'll be back for you, baby.

1340
01:48:20,361 --> 01:48:22,530
Get your hands off me!

1341
01:48:25,074 --> 01:48:27,952
Both corners furiously working
on their bots.

1342
01:48:28,119 --> 01:48:31,455
This crowd came here tonight
expecting a massacre,

1343
01:48:31,622 --> 01:48:33,624
but instead they're getting a war!

1344
01:48:33,791 --> 01:48:35,126
- You got it?
- Yeah.

1345
01:48:35,292 --> 01:48:36,293
All right. Here we go.

1346
01:48:36,460 --> 01:48:38,546
What is happening?

1347
01:48:38,712 --> 01:48:43,676
He is fully prepared for all possible
contingencies. He will be fine.

1348
01:48:43,843 --> 01:48:45,177
What next?

1349
01:48:46,095 --> 01:48:47,430
Round two.

1350
01:48:55,604 --> 01:48:58,899
Round two kicks off,
and incredibly the challenger, Atom,

1351
01:48:59,066 --> 01:49:01,068
is giving the champ a run for his money.

1352
01:49:02,820 --> 01:49:06,490
Zeus tosses the smaller bot
across the ring like a tin can!

1353
01:49:10,286 --> 01:49:15,207
Kenton working his bot with a trifecta
of straight rights to the champ's dome!

1354
01:49:20,337 --> 01:49:24,300
Toe-to-toe they stand,
trading deafening blows!

1355
01:49:27,386 --> 01:49:31,056
Whatever strategy either corner
had cooked up has been destroyed!

1356
01:49:33,893 --> 01:49:37,313
Metal bashing metal.
Steel smashing steel.

1357
01:49:37,480 --> 01:49:39,690
This is a brawl!

1358
01:49:42,443 --> 01:49:47,323
The crowd is on their feet, watching two
machines driven to kill each other!

1359
01:49:47,490 --> 01:49:50,034
Something has to give, and it does!

1360
01:49:50,201 --> 01:49:51,994
Atom goes down again!

1361
01:49:52,161 --> 01:49:56,248
Lights out for the junkyard dog who put
on a heck of a show here tonight!

1362
01:49:58,417 --> 01:50:00,961
And yet again, Atom rises up.

1363
01:50:01,128 --> 01:50:05,591
Kenton must have hardwired
this bot with the will to go on!

1364
01:50:12,056 --> 01:50:17,061
Midway through round four, and Zeus
is looking to end this thing right now.

1365
01:50:17,228 --> 01:50:21,565
The champ is holding nothing back
as he cracks open the hurt locker!

1366
01:50:31,742 --> 01:50:35,579
Atom is stumbling around the ring,
apparently disoriented and dazed!

1367
01:50:35,746 --> 01:50:37,206
- Hands up!
- What's going on?

1368
01:50:37,373 --> 01:50:40,251
I think the voice recog is shot!
He's not responding!

1369
01:50:43,587 --> 01:50:48,259
Zeus has found yet another gear of
violence, drilling Atom's midsection.

1370
01:50:48,425 --> 01:50:51,595
No! Stop! Do something!

1371
01:50:51,762 --> 01:50:52,763
He can't hear me!

1372
01:50:54,265 --> 01:50:59,770
But the bell sounds, and once again
this little robot has stunned the world!

1373
01:51:01,939 --> 01:51:06,402
We're done, Max! He can't hear me.
This is murder. We've had enough.

1374
01:51:06,569 --> 01:51:08,946
- I'm disabling the voice recognition.
- He can't hear me!

1375
01:51:09,113 --> 01:51:11,490
- Yes, but he can see you!
- What?

1376
01:51:12,908 --> 01:51:15,703
I'm putting him in shadow mode.
Show him what to do.

1377
01:51:15,869 --> 01:51:18,289
Without the voice recognition,
he'll move even faster!

1378
01:51:18,455 --> 01:51:19,623
No way. No way!

1379
01:51:19,790 --> 01:51:21,709
Look at them. They are freaking out!

1380
01:51:22,376 --> 01:51:24,461
Rich girl is ripping him
a new one over there!

1381
01:51:24,628 --> 01:51:26,630
Do you know why?
Because they're scared.

1382
01:51:26,797 --> 01:51:28,966
Because Atom can do things
no other bot has ever done.

1383
01:51:29,133 --> 01:51:30,926
- But I can't do it!
- Yes, you can.

1384
01:51:31,093 --> 01:51:33,804
- I can't.
- Yes, you can.

1385
01:51:34,972 --> 01:51:38,517
Show him what to do.
You have to fight the last round.

1386
01:51:38,684 --> 01:51:40,144
Don't ask me. Don't.

1387
01:51:40,311 --> 01:51:44,732
Charlie... please. I beg you.

1388
01:51:53,574 --> 01:51:54,974
Are you kidding me with those eyes?

1389
01:51:56,827 --> 01:51:58,329
Damn it!

1390
01:51:58,495 --> 01:51:59,538
Yes!

1391
01:52:00,289 --> 01:52:01,832
I can't believe I'm doing this.

1392
01:52:02,916 --> 01:52:05,478
I know you're in there! I'm not sure
if you're getting this or what,

1393
01:52:05,502 --> 01:52:06,754
but I know you're in there!

1394
01:52:06,920 --> 01:52:09,214
- Kenton. In or out?
- In. Give me a minute.

1395
01:52:12,801 --> 01:52:17,473
I know you can't hear me,
but you can see me, so watch me!

1396
01:52:17,640 --> 01:52:20,184
Watch... me.

1397
01:52:20,351 --> 01:52:23,854
- You know you're talking to a robot.
- I know. Shut up.

1398
01:52:25,022 --> 01:52:26,732
Watch me.

1399
01:52:27,066 --> 01:52:29,026
An epic battle being waged here tonight,

1400
01:52:29,193 --> 01:52:31,278
as the fifth and final round
gets underway.

1401
01:52:31,445 --> 01:52:32,988
Come on, Atom!

1402
01:52:42,623 --> 01:52:44,875
Wait a second. Are you seeing this?

1403
01:52:45,042 --> 01:52:48,128
Charlie Kenton is shadowboxing
just outside the ring!

1404
01:52:48,295 --> 01:52:50,547
It looks like Atom
has a shadow function.

1405
01:52:50,714 --> 01:52:53,467
So, basically,
that means Charlie Kenton

1406
01:52:53,634 --> 01:52:56,428
is fighting the last round
of this fight against Zeus.

1407
01:52:56,595 --> 01:53:01,058
It doesn't seem to help, because Atom
is backed up against the ropes again.

1408
01:53:03,143 --> 01:53:04,978
Help him! Fight back!

1409
01:53:05,145 --> 01:53:06,230
Not yet.

1410
01:53:09,775 --> 01:53:13,654
Tak Mashido supervising personally
as Zeus hammers down,

1411
01:53:13,821 --> 01:53:16,740
furiously trying to end this thing
once and for all.

1412
01:53:17,741 --> 01:53:20,744
I got to tell you, folks,
the champ looks tired.

1413
01:53:20,911 --> 01:53:23,205
This robot seems to be running on empty.

1414
01:53:27,042 --> 01:53:29,420
I don't believe it.
Atom is taunting Zeus.

1415
01:53:29,586 --> 01:53:33,090
- Switch to turbo!
- He's actually asking for more.

1416
01:53:35,092 --> 01:53:36,677
Please do something!

1417
01:53:36,844 --> 01:53:39,096
- Not yet.
- That's right, Charlie. Not yet.

1418
01:53:41,890 --> 01:53:43,267
Nitrous pistons, now!

1419
01:53:46,478 --> 01:53:48,439
He's not going to last much longer!

1420
01:53:48,605 --> 01:53:50,441
- Fight back!
- Not yet.

1421
01:53:51,191 --> 01:53:52,484
Hang in there!

1422
01:53:52,651 --> 01:53:57,948
Atom is riddled with the nitrous-fuelled
Gatling guns of Zeus's blows!

1423
01:53:59,199 --> 01:54:02,953
Atom! Atom! Atom! Atom!

1424
01:54:06,373 --> 01:54:08,500
Wait him out, wait him out! Not yet!

1425
01:54:11,086 --> 01:54:13,130
Zeus is slowing down!

1426
01:54:13,297 --> 01:54:16,133
The champ's power core
is clearly depleted.

1427
01:54:16,300 --> 01:54:17,301
Charlie, please!

1428
01:54:19,636 --> 01:54:20,763
Hey, kid.

1429
01:54:21,638 --> 01:54:23,056
- Now.
- Now!

1430
01:54:28,479 --> 01:54:29,480
Get in there!

1431
01:54:31,982 --> 01:54:34,318
Knock that little bitch! Bust him open!

1432
01:54:43,285 --> 01:54:44,661
Yeah! That's right!

1433
01:54:46,163 --> 01:54:47,414
Do something!

1434
01:54:48,332 --> 01:54:49,333
Move!

1435
01:54:50,834 --> 01:54:53,170
Override. Switching to manual.

1436
01:54:55,255 --> 01:55:00,010
In a shocking move, Tak Mashido is
manually operating his robot personally!

1437
01:55:10,646 --> 01:55:13,190
- Work the body! Get inside him!
- Get him, Atom!

1438
01:55:14,942 --> 01:55:19,530
Look at this! The champ is trying
desperately to stay on his feet,

1439
01:55:19,696 --> 01:55:24,868
but Kenton is relentless, landing
blow after blow after blow to the body!

1440
01:56:07,202 --> 01:56:09,371
Left! Right! Left! Right!

1441
01:56:09,538 --> 01:56:14,668
A huge uppercut by Atom! Zeus is down!

1442
01:56:19,339 --> 01:56:22,509
This little bot has
dug deep here tonight

1443
01:56:22,676 --> 01:56:25,304
and shown something damn near heart!

1444
01:56:25,470 --> 01:56:29,725
One, two, three,

1445
01:56:29,892 --> 01:56:34,771
four, five, six, seven...

1446
01:56:34,938 --> 01:56:35,939
He's good!

1447
01:56:36,106 --> 01:56:39,443
Zeus gets to his feet,
but Kenton has Atom on him again,

1448
01:56:39,610 --> 01:56:41,278
landing punch after punch!

1449
01:56:41,445 --> 01:56:43,906
Tak Mashido and his super bot
have no answer.

1450
01:56:44,072 --> 01:56:47,117
Zeus pins Atom's left arm,
but Kenton is undaunted!

1451
01:56:47,284 --> 01:56:50,203
It all comes down to this, folks!

1452
01:56:50,370 --> 01:56:52,205
Drop him, Charlie! Now!

1453
01:56:52,372 --> 01:56:55,334
- Kenton is about to drop the champ...
- No! There's the bell!

1454
01:56:56,460 --> 01:56:58,629
Zeus is saved by the bell!

1455
01:57:05,594 --> 01:57:08,388
Amazingly, we will go
to the judges' cards!

1456
01:57:22,110 --> 01:57:25,989
Ladies and gentlemen,
after five rounds,

1457
01:57:26,156 --> 01:57:28,825
we go to the judges' scorecards.

1458
01:57:32,788 --> 01:57:37,167
Judge Number One scores the fight 47-48.

1459
01:57:37,334 --> 01:57:42,255
Judge Number Two scores the fight 48-46.

1460
01:57:42,422 --> 01:57:47,052
And Judge Number Three
scores the fight 47-46,

1461
01:57:47,219 --> 01:57:52,432
for the winner
and still World Robot Boxing champion,

1462
01:57:52,599 --> 01:57:54,935
Zeus!

1463
01:58:02,317 --> 01:58:04,486
Farra Lemkova,

1464
01:58:04,653 --> 01:58:06,947
you got way more
than you bargained for tonight.

1465
01:58:07,114 --> 01:58:10,534
Some would say that your bot
won the decision but lost the fight.

1466
01:58:11,284 --> 01:58:12,577
She looks pissed.

1467
01:58:13,245 --> 01:58:15,539
It took a little longer
than we thought,

1468
01:58:15,706 --> 01:58:18,875
but the result is as expected.

1469
01:58:20,210 --> 01:58:24,631
We won. Zeus is still undefeated.

1470
01:58:30,053 --> 01:58:33,181
Any comment on the absolutely
humiliating near loss

1471
01:58:33,348 --> 01:58:34,599
your bot suffered tonight?

1472
01:58:37,686 --> 01:58:40,147
- Nothing.
- No comment.

1473
01:58:40,313 --> 01:58:41,732
Max. Where's Max?

1474
01:58:45,318 --> 01:58:46,528
There he is. Max.

1475
01:58:48,238 --> 01:58:51,742
They're already calling your bot
"the people's champion."

1476
01:58:55,162 --> 01:58:57,080
What do you say to that?

1477
01:58:58,081 --> 01:58:59,416
People's champion?

1478
01:59:02,002 --> 01:59:03,420
Sounds pretty good to me.

1479
01:59:09,301 --> 01:59:11,344
Dad? Dad!

1480
01:59:15,390 --> 01:59:16,558
Dad!

1481
01:59:27,444 --> 01:59:29,112
I really want you to know...

1482
01:59:29,279 --> 01:59:31,281
No, I need you to know.

1483
01:59:33,450 --> 01:59:34,743
Don't worry.

1484
01:59:35,786 --> 01:59:37,454
Your secret's safe with me.

1485
01:59:44,503 --> 01:59:46,171
Wait here. Wait here.

1486
02:00:31,049 --> 02:00:32,676
Yes!

